    <div class="divider"></div>

    <div style="display:flex; flex-direction:column; gap:14px;">

      <div class="study-card">
        <div style="display:flex; align-items:flex-start; justify-content:space-between; gap:12px; flex-wrap:wrap;">
          <div class="study-journal">CHEST Journal &mdash; February 2021</div>
          <div style="display:flex; gap:7px; flex-wrap:wrap;">
            <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/33539839/" target="_blank" style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:4px;background:#0a3d6b;color:#fff;font-size:10.5px;font-weight:700;padding:4px 11px;border-radius:20px;text-decoration:none;letter-spacing:.04em;">&#128279; PubMed</a>
            <a href="https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC8411450/" target="_blank" style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:4px;background:#27ae60;color:#fff;font-size:10.5px;font-weight:700;padding:4px 11px;border-radius:20px;text-decoration:none;letter-spacing:.04em;">&#128214; Free Full Text</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="study-title">Validation of a Novel Compact System for the Measurement of Lung Volumes</div>
        <div class="study-authors">Kenneth I. Berger MD (NYU), Ori Adam PhD, David A. Kaminsky MD, Robert J. Shiner MD, Felip Burgos PhD, Frans H.C. de Jongh PhD, Inon Cohen PhD, Jeffrey J. Fredberg PhD (Harvard)</div>
        <div class="study-finding"><strong>Key finding:</strong> TLC measured by the MiniBox+ is not significantly different from conventional body plethysmography across 266 participants at 5 global medical centers &mdash; including patients with obstructive and restrictive disease. MiniBox+ volumes correlated better with the body box than any other office-based alternative. In 10 of 14 cases where device results differed, the MiniBox+ diagnosis was more clinically accurate.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="study-card">
        <div style="display:flex; align-items:flex-start; justify-content:space-between; gap:12px; flex-wrap:wrap;">
          <div class="study-journal">Clinicoecon Outcomes Research &mdash; July 2021 (Verona, Italy)</div>
          <div style="display:flex; gap:7px; flex-wrap:wrap;">
            <a href="https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC8275122/" target="_blank" style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:4px;background:#27ae60;color:#fff;font-size:10.5px;font-weight:700;padding:4px 11px;border-radius:20px;text-decoration:none;letter-spacing:.04em;">&#128214; Free Full Text</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="study-title">Comparison of Consistency, Feasibility, and Convenience of a Novel Compact System vs. Whole Body Plethysmography</div>
        <div class="study-authors">Roberto W. Dal Negro MD, Paola Turco, Massimiliano Povero &mdash; 134 patients, Specialist Medical Centre, Verona</div>
        <div class="study-finding"><strong>Key findings:</strong> MiniBox+ had <strong>significantly lower failure risk</strong> (8.21% vs. 19.4% for body box). Average test time was <strong>7.2 min vs. 13.9 min</strong> for body box. Cost per test was lower with MiniBox+ (&#8364;75.11 vs. &#8364;87.58). TLC and DLco values were highly consistent between both methods with clinically negligible differences.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="study-card">
        <div style="display:flex; align-items:flex-start; justify-content:space-between; gap:12px; flex-wrap:wrap;">
          <div class="study-journal">VA Medical Center Cincinnati &mdash; USA Study</div>
          <span style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:4px;background:#f4f6f9;color:#5a6a7a;font-size:10.5px;font-weight:600;padding:4px 11px;border-radius:20px;border:1px solid #e8ecf0;letter-spacing:.04em;">&#128196; Internal Data on File</span>
        </div>
        <div class="study-title">MiniBox TLC vs. Body Plethysmography (MGC Diagnostics) &mdash; 50 Subjects</div>
        <div class="study-authors">Conducted at the VA Medical Center, Cincinnati, OH</div>
        <div class="study-finding"><strong>Key finding:</strong> MiniBox TLC correlated well with body box TLC (adjusted r&#178; = 0.85). CV of 9.1% &mdash; lower than the multi-center study CV of 12.1% and significantly lower than Helium Dilution (18.9%) and CT (15.6%) compared to body plethysmography.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="study-card">
        <div style="display:flex; align-items:flex-start; justify-content:space-between; gap:12px; flex-wrap:wrap;">
          <div class="study-journal">Massachusetts General Hospital &mdash; Boston, USA</div>
          <span style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:4px;background:#f4f6f9;color:#5a6a7a;font-size:10.5px;font-weight:600;padding:4px 11px;border-radius:20px;border:1px solid #e8ecf0;letter-spacing:.04em;">&#128196; Internal Data on File</span>
        </div>
        <div class="study-title">MiniBox TLC vs. Body Plethysmography (Morgan Scientific) &mdash; 27 Subjects</div>
        <div class="study-authors">Conducted by Dr. David J. Kanarek, Pulmonologist, MGH Boston</div>
        <div class="study-finding"><strong>Key finding:</strong> MiniBox TLC correlated well with body box TLC (adjusted r&#178; = 0.85). CV of 10.9%. Results consistent with the multi-center validation data.</div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- COMPETITIVE -->
  <div class="tab-panel" id="tab-competitive">
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="section-icon icon-amber">&#9878;</div>
      <div>
        <div class="section-title">Competitive Landscape</div>
        <div class="section-sub">Every major player, their costs, and how MiniBox+ wins against each one &mdash; prices from 2023 deck, verify before use</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- OBJECTION HANDLERS -->
    <div class="alert-box alert-amber" style="margin-bottom:10px;">
      <div class="alert-icon">&#9888;</div>
      <div><strong>"We already have a body box."</strong> &mdash; The MiniBox+ is a complement, not a replacement. Run complete PFTs in satellite offices and exam rooms where a body box can't go. Half the cost, zero maintenance, any staff can operate it. CHEST 2021 validated equivalent to the body box in 700+ patients at 11 medical centers.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="alert-box alert-blue">
      <div class="alert-icon">&#128161;</div>
      <div><strong>Critical for COPD/Asthma practices:</strong> N&#8322; Washout and Helium Dilution systematically underestimate lung volumes in obstructive disease &mdash; gas can't reach trapped air. MiniBox+ plethysmography measures ALL gas in the thorax. Truer disease picture, and you can bill the higher CPT 94726 code vs. lower-paying 94727.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="divider"></div>

