  <!-- IT & CONNECTIVITY -->
  <div class="tab-panel" id="tab-it">
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="section-icon icon-blue">&#128279;</div>
      <div>
        <div class="section-title">IT &amp; Connectivity</div>
        <div class="section-sub">HL7 integration, tablet specs, security architecture, and network requirements for IT departments</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="alert-box alert-blue">
      <div class="alert-icon">&#9432;</div>
      <div><strong>Key message for IT:</strong> The MiniBox+ operates in standalone mode with zero IT infrastructure required. HL7 EMR integration is optional and adds no complexity to the base device. All HL7 software is built into the tablet &mdash; no external servers needed. Connection is TCP/IP over Wi-Fi to the practice's existing EMR server.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="section-head" style="margin-top:8px;">
      <div class="section-icon icon-teal">&#128203;</div>
      <div>
        <div class="section-title">HL7 Integration Overview</div>
        <div class="section-sub">PUO-DOC20130 Rev. 01 &mdash; September 2024</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card-grid grid-3">
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title">HL7 Standard</div>
        <div class="card-body">Supports <strong>HL7 v2.5.1</strong> natively. Also successfully integrated with HL7 v2.3 and v2.4. Compatible with higher versions &mdash; contact PulmOne for guidance.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title">Connection Type</div>
        <div class="card-body"><strong>TCP/IP over Wi-Fi.</strong> MiniBox listening port: <strong>8080</strong> (configurable). Static IP assignment recommended via DHCP to prevent connectivity loss after power failure or network maintenance.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title">Operating Mode</div>
        <div class="card-body">Works in <strong>standalone mode</strong> (no network required) or as an <strong>HL7 client</strong> connected to the practice EMR. All HL7 software is built into the MiniBox tablet &mdash; no external servers required.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="divider"></div>

    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="section-icon icon-teal">&#8646;</div>
      <div>
        <div class="section-title">Data Flow: What Goes In and What Comes Out</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card-grid grid-2">
      <div class="card" style="border-left:4px solid var(--blue-brand);">
        <div class="card-title" style="color:var(--blue-brand);">&#8594; EMR to MiniBox (ORMO01 Order Message)</div>
        <div class="card-body" style="margin-bottom:10px;">The EMR sends patient demographic and order information to the MiniBox before the test begins. This pre-populates the patient record automatically.</div>
        <div class="card-body"><strong>Required fields:</strong> Patient ID, Patient Name, Date of Birth, Sex, Message Type (ORM^O01), Universal Service ID (e.g., PFT13^COMPLETE PULMONARY FUNCTION TEST).</div>
        <div style="margin-top:10px; padding:10px; background:var(--gray-100); border-radius:6px; font-family:'DM Mono',monospace; font-size:11px; line-height:1.7; color:#374151;">
          Valid test order codes:<br>
          PFT13^COMPLETE PULMONARY FUNCTION TEST &rarr; FVC + LVM + DLCO<br>
          PulmOneSPR^Pulm One Spirometry &rarr; FVC only<br>
          PulmOneSVC^Pulm One Slow Vital &rarr; SVC only<br>
          PulmOneMVV^Pulm One Voluntary &rarr; MVV only<br>
          PFT Full &rarr; FVC + LVM + DLCO
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="card" style="border-left:4px solid var(--teal);">
        <div class="card-title" style="color:var(--teal);">&#8592; MiniBox to EMR (ORUR01 Results Message)</div>
        <div class="card-body" style="margin-bottom:10px;">After testing, the MiniBox automatically sends results back to the EMR. No manual data entry required.</div>
        <div class="card-body"><strong>What is transmitted per parameter:</strong> Best measured value, Predicted value, % Predicted, Lower Limit of Normal (LLN), Upper Limit of Normal (ULN), and Z-Score.</div>
        <div style="margin-top:10px; padding:10px; background:var(--gray-100); border-radius:6px; font-size:13px; color:#374151;">
          <strong>Also included:</strong> Full visit summary PDF report encoded in Base64 within the ORUR01 message &mdash; OR stored on a network drive with the filename embedded in the message. Pre and Post bronchodilator values sent as separate OBX segments.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="divider"></div>

    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="section-icon icon-amber">&#128274;</div>
      <div>
        <div class="section-title">Security Architecture</div>
        <div class="section-sub">MDS2 Disclosure &mdash; SW Versions 3.2.0.0 to 3.3.0.0 &mdash; January 30, 2025</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card-grid grid-3">
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title">Data Encryption</div>
        <div class="card-body">Patient data stored in an encrypted SQLite database on the tablet's internal drive. Local encryption via <strong>Windows BitLocker.</strong> Data partitioned separately from the operating system.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title">User Authentication</div>
        <div class="card-body">Role-based access control (Admin and General roles). Password minimum 8 characters with uppercase, lowercase, digit, and special character required. <strong>Account locked after 5 failed attempts.</strong> Passwords expire after 90 days.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title">Auto Logoff</div>
        <div class="card-body">Automatic logoff after <strong>15 minutes of inactivity</strong> (configurable). System returns to home screen. Configurable with assistance from PulmOne Customer Support.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title">Audit Logging</div>
        <div class="card-body">Audit log records: successful and unsuccessful logins, user creation/modification/deletion, data import/export via USB, HL7 data transmission, and software updates. Log exportable via USB. Requires admin privileges to access.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title">Kiosk Mode</div>
        <div class="card-body">Device operates in <strong>Windows Kiosk Mode by default.</strong> Operators can only access the MiniBox application. Windows admin password required to exit Kiosk mode and install any third-party software.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title">Network Security</div>
        <div class="card-body">Windows Firewall enabled. Wi-Fi with WPA/WPA2 authentication. <strong>No internet connection required</strong> for PFT testing. Device does not communicate with external networks outside of HL7 to the local EMR server.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="alert-box alert-amber" style="margin-top:16px;">
      <div class="alert-icon">&#9888;</div>
      <div><strong>HL7 data in transit is not encrypted.</strong> PulmOne recommends HL7 communication occur within the practice's internal network. The device does not transmit ePHI over the internet. Full MDS2 disclosure document available on request from PulmOne (PUO-DOCXXXXX, Jan 30, 2025).</div>
    </div>

    <div class="divider"></div>

    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="section-icon icon-blue">&#128187;</div>
      <div>
        <div class="section-title">Tablet: Microsoft Surface Go 4</div>
        <div class="section-sub">PulmOne-validated tablet running MiniBox+ software &mdash; performance tested June 2024</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card-grid grid-2">
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title">Hardware Specifications</div>
        <div class="card-body">
          <table style="width:100%; font-size:13px; border-collapse:collapse;">
            <tr style="border-bottom:1px solid var(--gray-200);"><td style="padding:5px 0; color:var(--gray-600); width:45%;">CPU</td><td style="padding:5px 0; font-weight:500;">Intel N200, Quad Core, Max 3.7 GHz</td></tr>
            <tr style="border-bottom:1px solid var(--gray-200);"><td style="padding:5px 0; color:var(--gray-600);">RAM</td><td style="padding:5px 0; font-weight:500;">8GB LPDDR5</td></tr>
            <tr style="border-bottom:1px solid var(--gray-200);"><td style="padding:5px 0; color:var(--gray-600);">Storage</td><td style="padding:5px 0; font-weight:500;">128GB UFS Drive</td></tr>
            <tr style="border-bottom:1px solid var(--gray-200);"><td style="padding:5px 0; color:var(--gray-600);">Display</td><td style="padding:5px 0; font-weight:500;">10.5" PixelSense 1920x1280 touchscreen</td></tr>
            <tr style="border-bottom:1px solid var(--gray-200);"><td style="padding:5px 0; color:var(--gray-600);">OS</td><td style="padding:5px 0; font-weight:500;">Windows 11 Pro</td></tr>
            <tr style="border-bottom:1px solid var(--gray-200);"><td style="padding:5px 0; color:var(--gray-600);">Wi-Fi</td><td style="padding:5px 0; font-weight:500;">Wi-Fi 6 (802.11ax)</td></tr>
            <tr style="border-bottom:1px solid var(--gray-200);"><td style="padding:5px 0; color:var(--gray-600);">Security</td><td style="padding:5px 0; font-weight:500;">TPM 2.0, BitLocker, Windows Secured-core PC</td></tr>
            <tr><td style="padding:5px 0; color:var(--gray-600);">Weight</td><td style="padding:5px 0; font-weight:500;">1.15 lbs (521g)</td></tr>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title">Performance Test Results vs. Surface Go 3</div>
        <div class="card-body" style="margin-bottom:10px;">PulmOne formally tested the Surface Go 4 against the Surface Go 3 (the previous MiniBox tablet) in June 2024. The Go 4 was approved as the replacement tablet for all MiniBox+ units.</div>
        <table style="width:100%; font-size:12.5px; border-collapse:collapse;">
          <thead><tr style="background:var(--blue-dark);">
            <th style="padding:8px 10px; text-align:left; color:#fff; font-weight:600; font-size:11px;">Test</th>
            <th style="padding:8px 10px; text-align:center; color:#fff; font-weight:600; font-size:11px;">Go 4</th>
            <th style="padding:8px 10px; text-align:center; color:#fff; font-weight:600; font-size:11px;">Go 3</th>
            <th style="padding:8px 10px; text-align:center; color:#5bc8f5; font-weight:600; font-size:11px;">Delta</th>
          </tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr style="border-bottom:1px solid var(--gray-200);"><td style="padding:7px 10px; color:var(--gray-600);">Overall</td><td style="text-align:center; padding:7px 10px; font-weight:500;">1308</td><td style="text-align:center; padding:7px 10px;">1118</td><td style="text-align:center; padding:7px 10px; color:var(--green); font-weight:600;">+16.9%</td></tr>
            <tr style="border-bottom:1px solid var(--gray-200); background:var(--green-light);"><td style="padding:7px 10px; color:var(--gray-600);">CPU</td><td style="text-align:center; padding:7px 10px; font-weight:700; color:var(--green);">5300</td><td style="text-align:center; padding:7px 10px;">2973</td><td style="text-align:center; padding:7px 10px; color:var(--green); font-weight:700;">+78.2%</td></tr>
            <tr style="border-bottom:1px solid var(--gray-200);"><td style="padding:7px 10px; color:var(--gray-600);">2D Graphics</td><td style="text-align:center; padding:7px 10px; font-weight:500;">162</td><td style="text-align:center; padding:7px 10px;">109</td><td style="text-align:center; padding:7px 10px; color:var(--green); font-weight:600;">+48.6%</td></tr>
            <tr style="border-bottom:1px solid var(--gray-200);"><td style="padding:7px 10px; color:var(--gray-600);">Memory</td><td style="text-align:center; padding:7px 10px; font-weight:500;">1709</td><td style="text-align:center; padding:7px 10px;">1644</td><td style="text-align:center; padding:7px 10px; color:var(--green); font-weight:600;">+3.9%</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        <div style="margin-top:10px; font-size:12px; color:var(--gray-600);">Conclusion from PulmOne test report: "The Surface Go 4 can run MiniBox+ software reliably with similar or better performance than the existing tablet."</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="divider"></div>

    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="section-icon icon-green">&#9989;</div>
      <div>
        <div class="section-title">IT Checklist for HL7 Rollout</div>
        <div class="section-sub">What the practice IT team needs to do to enable HL7 integration</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card-grid grid-2">
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title">Network Requirements</div>
        <div class="card-body">
          <ul style="list-style:none; display:flex; flex-direction:column; gap:8px;">
            <li style="display:flex; gap:10px; font-size:13px;"><span style="color:var(--green); font-weight:700; flex-shrink:0;">&#10003;</span> Assign static IP to MiniBox tablet via DHCP</li>
            <li style="display:flex; gap:10px; font-size:13px;"><span style="color:var(--green); font-weight:700; flex-shrink:0;">&#10003;</span> Open firewall: allow TCP from EMR server IP to MiniBox port 8080</li>
            <li style="display:flex; gap:10px; font-size:13px;"><span style="color:var(--green); font-weight:700; flex-shrink:0;">&#10003;</span> Open firewall: allow TCP from MiniBox IP to EMR results interface port</li>
            <li style="display:flex; gap:10px; font-size:13px;"><span style="color:var(--green); font-weight:700; flex-shrink:0;">&#10003;</span> Ensure Wi-Fi 6 access point in testing room</li>
            <li style="display:flex; gap:10px; font-size:13px;"><span style="color:var(--green); font-weight:700; flex-shrink:0;">&#10003;</span> WPA/WPA2 authentication on wireless network</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title">EMR Configuration</div>
        <div class="card-body">
          <ul style="list-style:none; display:flex; flex-direction:column; gap:8px;">
            <li style="display:flex; gap:10px; font-size:13px;"><span style="color:var(--green); font-weight:700; flex-shrink:0;">&#10003;</span> Configure HL7 order interface to send ORMO01 messages to MiniBox IP:8080</li>
            <li style="display:flex; gap:10px; font-size:13px;"><span style="color:var(--green); font-weight:700; flex-shrink:0;">&#10003;</span> Configure HL7 results interface to receive ORUR01 from MiniBox</li>
            <li style="display:flex; gap:10px; font-size:13px;"><span style="color:var(--green); font-weight:700; flex-shrink:0;">&#10003;</span> Set Universal Service ID to PFT13^COMPLETE PULMONARY FUNCTION TEST for full panel</li>
            <li style="display:flex; gap:10px; font-size:13px;"><span style="color:var(--green); font-weight:700; flex-shrink:0;">&#10003;</span> Contact PulmOne for configuration support &mdash; <a href="mailto:service@pulm-one.com">service@pulm-one.com</a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>

  <!-- TROUBLESHOOTING -->
  <div class="tab-panel" id="tab-troubleshooting">
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="section-icon icon-amber">&#9888;</div>
      <div>
        <div class="section-title">Troubleshooting Guide</div>
        <div class="section-sub">Error codes, hardware failures, and step-by-step fixes for common MiniBox+ issues</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="alert-box alert-amber">
      <div class="alert-icon">&#9888;</div>
      <div><strong>If a device cannot be resolved remotely,</strong> it must be sent in for repair. Contact PulmOne at <strong>1-844-PulmOne (785-6663)</strong> or <strong><a href="mailto:service@pulm-one.com">service@pulm-one.com</a></strong> to initiate a service order.</div>
    </div>

    <!-- EC102G -->
    <div class="coaching-card">
      <div class="coaching-header" style="background:#fff5f5;">
        <span class="coaching-tag" style="background:#fde8e6; color:#c0392b;">EC102G</span>
        <div>
          <div class="coaching-name">HUB Board Error</div>
          <div class="coaching-desc">Communication failure on the HUB board.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="coaching-body">
        <div>
          <div class="coaching-col-title">Remote Steps</div>
          <ul class="coaching-list">
            <li><div class="cli-num">1</div> Ask customer to disconnect everything.</li>
            <li><div class="cli-num">2</div> Reconnect all cables.</li>
            <li><div class="cli-num">3</div> Restart the device completely.</li>
            <li><div class="cli-num">4</div> Perform 2 successful DLCO tests to confirm resolution.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="coaching-col-title">If Error Persists</div>
          <ul class="coaching-list">
            <li><div class="cli-dot" style="color:#c0392b;">&#8226;</div> <span class="highlight">Device must come in for HUB board repair.</span></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- EC117 -->
    <div class="coaching-card">
      <div class="coaching-header" style="background:#fff5f5;">
        <span class="coaching-tag" style="background:#fde8e6; color:#c0392b;">EC117</span>
        <div>
          <div class="coaching-name">Gas Analyzer Issue</div>
          <div class="coaching-desc">Internal gas system error.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="coaching-body">
        <div>
          <div class="coaching-col-title">Remote Steps</div>
          <ul class="coaching-list">
            <li><div class="cli-num">1</div> Have the customer restart the tablet.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="coaching-col-title">If Error Persists</div>
          <ul class="coaching-list">
            <li><div class="cli-dot" style="color:#c0392b;">&#8226;</div> <span class="highlight">Device must come in for repair.</span> Replace Gas Analyzer.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- EC11H -->
    <div class="coaching-card">
      <div class="coaching-header" style="background:#fff5f5;">
        <span class="coaching-tag" style="background:#fde8e6; color:#c0392b;">EC11H</span>
        <div>
          <div class="coaching-name">HHU Connection Error</div>
          <div class="coaching-desc">HHU not communicating with MiniBox+.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="coaching-body">
        <div>
          <div class="coaching-col-title">Remote Steps</div>
          <ul class="coaching-list">
            <li><div class="cli-num">1</div> Disconnect the HHU.</li>
            <li><div class="cli-num">2</div> Reconnect the HHU securely.</li>
            <li><div class="cli-num">3</div> Restart the device and confirm error is gone.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="coaching-col-title">If Error Persists</div>
          <ul class="coaching-list">
            <li><div class="cli-dot" style="color:#c0392b;">&#8226;</div> Send only the HHU in for repair, <strong>or</strong></li>
            <li><div class="cli-dot" style="color:#c0392b;">&#8226;</div> Ship a replacement HHU to the customer.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- EC11M -->
    <div class="coaching-card">
      <div class="coaching-header" style="background:#fff5f5;">
        <span class="coaching-tag" style="background:#fde8e6; color:#c0392b;">EC11M</span>
        <div>
          <div class="coaching-name">Communication Port Error</div>
          <div class="coaching-desc">CU port or communication cable issue. Check for physical damage.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="coaching-body">
        <div>
          <div class="coaching-col-title">Remote Steps</div>
          <ul class="coaching-list">
            <li><div class="cli-num">1</div> Turn off the device.</li>
            <li><div class="cli-num">2</div> Disconnect all communication cables.</li>
            <li><div class="cli-num">3</div> Ask customer to send a photo of the back of the device &mdash; check if CU port is damaged.</li>
            <li><div class="cli-num">4</div> Wait 10 seconds, then power the device back on.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="coaching-col-title">If Error Persists</div>
          <ul class="coaching-list">
            <li><div class="cli-dot" style="color:#c0392b;">&#8226;</div> <span class="highlight">Device must come in for repair.</span></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="divider"></div>

    <!-- CO CH4 Low -->
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="section-icon icon-amber">&#128197;</div>
      <div>
        <div class="section-title">CO and CH&#8324; Concentration Low</div>
        <div class="section-sub">Work through each step in order before escalating to a repair</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card-grid grid-2">
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title">Step 1 &mdash; Verify Gas Mixture</div>
        <div class="card-body">Confirm the tank contains the correct mixture:<br><br>
          &bull; <strong>0.3%</strong> Methane (CH&#8324;)<br>
          &bull; <strong>0.3%</strong> Carbon Monoxide (CO)<br>
          &bull; <strong>21%</strong> Oxygen (O&#8322;)<br>
          &bull; Balanced Nitrogen (N&#8322;)<br>
          &bull; <strong>2% Accuracy</strong> Medical Grade
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title">Step 2 &mdash; Check Tank Pressure &amp; Volume</div>
        <div class="card-body">Verify both gauges on the regulator:<br><br>
          &bull; <strong>Left gauge (Pressure):</strong> 70&ndash;75 PSI<br>
          &bull; <strong>Right gauge (Volume):</strong> Above 500 PSI<br><br>
          If either reading is out of range, replace or refill the tank before proceeding.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title">Step 3 &mdash; Purge / Bleed the Gas Line</div>
        <div class="card-body">
          1. Turn off the gas tank completely.<br>
          2. Use the white knob to decrease pressure as far as it will go.<br>
          3. Disconnect the gas tubing from the regulator: press up the tiny black O-ring, then pull the tubing downward.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title">Step 4 &mdash; Cubic App Recalibration (Pre-2023 Devices Only)</div>
        <div class="card-body">If steps 1&ndash;3 don't resolve and device is <strong>older than 2023</strong>, use Cubic's app to recalibrate the gas analyzer. Watch the Cubic app training video first.<br><br>
          If the app still shows low CO and CH&#8324;: <span class="highlight">device must come in for repair.</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="divider"></div>

    <!-- Hardware failures -->
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="section-icon icon-amber" style="background:#fde8e6;">&#128268;</div>
      <div>
        <div class="section-title">Hardware Failures &mdash; No Remote Fix</div>
        <div class="section-sub">These cannot be resolved remotely. Device must be sent in.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card-grid grid-2">
      <div class="card" style="border-left:4px solid var(--red);">
        <div class="card-title" style="color:#c0392b;">Main Board Watchdog Error</div>
        <div class="card-body">The main board has failed. <strong>Device must come in for repair.</strong> Action: replace the mainboard.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card" style="border-left:4px solid var(--red);">
        <div class="card-title" style="color:#c0392b;">Sensor Board Watchdog Error</div>
        <div class="card-body">The sensor has gone bad. <strong>HHU must be replaced.</strong> Ship a replacement HHU or have the unit returned for repair.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="divider"></div>

    <!-- Common test failures -->
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="section-icon icon-amber">&#9888;</div>
      <div>
        <div class="section-title">Common Test Failure Reasons &amp; Fixes</div>
        <div class="section-sub">Patient coaching corrections for FVC, LVM, and DLCO failures</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card-grid grid-2">
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title" style="color:#c0392b;">FVC &mdash; Don't hesitate, exhale faster</div>
        <div class="card-body">Patient paused at the top of inhalation (Evol exceeded 5% of FVC). Fix: coach them to <strong>immediately blast</strong> air out the moment they reach peak inhalation &mdash; zero hesitation.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title" style="color:#c0392b;">FVC &mdash; End-of-test criteria not found</div>
        <div class="card-body">Patient stopped exhaling before plateau was reached. Fix: <strong>"Keep going, blow out every last bit of air."</strong> Common in COPD patients with prolonged expiratory time.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title" style="color:#c0392b;">LVM &mdash; TGV line not established</div>
        <div class="card-body">Tidal breathing was irregular before the maneuver. Fix: <strong>delete this test result</strong> (manual specifically recommends it). Let patient settle, then restart.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title" style="color:#c0392b;">DLCO &mdash; Couldn't find stable parameters</div>
        <div class="card-body">The 4 required tidal breaths were skipped or unsteady. Fix: reinforce the full sequence. <strong>Do NOT rush</strong> the patient. Wait the full 4 minutes before repeating.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>


  <!-- ==================== FORMS TAB ==================== -->
  <div class="tab-panel" id="tab-forms">
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="section-icon icon-green">&#128203;</div>
      <div>
        <div class="section-title">Forms &amp; Materials</div>
        <div class="section-sub">Every official PDF ready to view, download, or email &mdash; plus fill-and-print forms, no Excel needed</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ==================== v3.0 MATERIALS LIBRARY ==================== -->
    <div class="form-card" style="margin-bottom: 28px;">
      <div class="form-card-header" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0f2a1c, #15803d);">
        <div>
          <div class="form-card-title">&#128193; Materials Library</div>
          <div class="form-card-sub">The official PulmOne send-pack &mdash; one copy, always current, built into the toolkit</div>
        </div>
        <div style="display:flex; gap:8px; align-items:center;">
          <span style="font-size:11px; color:rgba(255,255,255,0.7); letter-spacing:0.06em;">REAL FILES &middot; ATTACH FROM ANY EMAIL</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="form-body">
        <div id="m3-library"><!-- rendered by toolkit v3 engine --></div>
      </div>
    </div>



    <!-- ==================== RMA / REPLACEMENT REQUEST (embedded v1.5: Pointer-Events signature w/ stylus support, Draw/Type cursive mode, photo attach embedded into PDF) ==================== -->
    <div class="form-card" style="margin-bottom: 28px;">
      <div class="form-card-header" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0a3d6b, #0e6abf);">
        <div>
          <div class="form-card-title">&#128295; MiniBox+&#8482; Replacement Request (RMA)</div>
          <div class="form-card-sub">Fill in &middot; sign on screen &middot; add photos &middot; send &mdash; v1.5</div>
        </div>
        <div style="display:flex; gap:8px; align-items:center; flex-wrap:wrap;">
          <span style="font-size:11px; color:rgba(255,255,255,0.7); letter-spacing:0.06em;">EMBEDDED</span>
          <button onclick="rmaFullscreen()" style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.15); border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.3); color:#fff; border-radius:6px; padding:7px 14px; font-family:'Inter',sans-serif; font-size:11.5px; font-weight:600; cursor:pointer;">&#9974; Fullscreen</button>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="form-body" style="padding: 0;">
        <div style="background:#f1f5f9; padding:10px 18px; font-size:12px; color:#475569; border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">
          &#9432; Type in the customer&rsquo;s details, sign on screen, then <strong>Send to PulmOne</strong> &mdash; on an iPad it opens your share sheet with the completed PDF attached; on a computer it saves the PDF and opens a pre-addressed email to service@pulm-one.com. (Customer auto-fill is coming in a later version.)
        </div>
        <iframe id="rma-iframe" allow="web-share; fullscreen; clipboard-write"
          style="width:100%; border:0; height:2250px; display:block; background:#eef2f7;"
          srcdoc="&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
&lt;html lang=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
&lt;head&gt;
&lt;meta charset=&quot;UTF-8&quot;&gt;
&lt;meta name=&quot;viewport&quot; content=&quot;width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0&quot;&gt;
&lt;title&gt;PulmOne USA &amp;mdash; MiniBox+ Replacement Request (RMA) v1.5&lt;/title&gt;
&lt;style&gt;
  @import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700&amp;display=swap');
  * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
  :root {
    --blue-dark:#0a3d6b; --blue-mid:#0c5299; --blue-brand:#0e6abf; --blue-light:#d6eaf8;
    --green:#27ae60; --amber:#e67e22; --red:#c0392b;
    --gray-100:#f4f6f9; --gray-200:#e8ecf0; --gray-300:#c8d0d8; --gray-600:#5a6a7a; --gray-800:#1e2d3d; --text:#1a2733;
  }
  body { font-family:'Inter',sans-serif; background:#eef2f7; color:var(--text); min-height:100vh; padding:22px 0; line-height:1.5; }
  .page { max-width:920px; margin:0 auto; padding:0 22px; }

  .site-header { background:var(--blue-dark); border-radius:10px 10px 0 0; padding:22px 28px; color:#fff; }
  .header-brand { font-size:11px; font-weight:600; letter-spacing:0.16em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#7ab6e0; margin-bottom:4px; }
  .header-title { font-size:23px; font-weight:700; line-height:1.2; }
  .header-sub { font-size:13px; color:#a8d0ee; margin-top:5px; }

  .form-card { background:#fff; border-radius:0 0 10px 10px; box-shadow:0 2px 12px rgba(10,61,107,0.08); border:1px solid var(--gray-200); border-top:none; padding:0 0 8px; }

  .section { padding:22px 28px 4px; }
  .section + .section { border-top:1px solid var(--gray-200); }
  .sec-title { font-size:15px; font-weight:700; color:var(--blue-dark); margin-bottom:4px; }
  .sec-hint { font-size:12.5px; color:var(--gray-600); margin-bottom:14px; }

  .grid2 { display:grid; grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr; gap:14px 18px; }
  @media(max-width:620px){ .grid2{ grid-template-columns:1fr; } }
  .field { display:flex; flex-direction:column; }
  .field.full { grid-column:1 / -1; }
  label.fld { font-size:11px; font-weight:700; color:var(--gray-600); text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.5px; margin-bottom:5px; }
  input[type=text], input[type=email], input[type=tel], input[type=date], textarea {
    width:100%; padding:11px 12px; font-size:14.5px; border:1px solid var(--gray-300); border-radius:8px; background:#fff; color:var(--text); font-family:inherit;
  }
  input:focus, textarea:focus { outline:2px solid var(--blue-brand); outline-offset:1px; border-color:var(--blue-brand); }
  textarea { min-height:96px; resize:vertical; }

  .alert { background:#fff7e6; border:1px solid #f3d39a; border-radius:8px; padding:13px 15px; font-size:12.5px; color:#7a4d00; line-height:1.6; margin-bottom:8px; }
  .alert strong { color:#8a3b00; }
  .alert.red { background:#fdecea; border-color:#f3b9b2; color:#8a1c12; }

  /* ITEM TABLE */
  .items { margin-top:4px; }
  .item-row { display:flex; align-items:center; gap:12px; padding:12px 14px; border:1px solid var(--gray-200); border-radius:9px; margin-bottom:10px; background:var(--gray-100); }
  .item-row.checked { background:#eaf5ff; border-color:#bcdcf7; }
  .item-row .chk { width:22px; height:22px; flex:0 0 auto; cursor:pointer; accent-color:var(--blue-brand); }
  .item-main { flex:1; min-width:0; }
  .item-name { font-size:14px; font-weight:600; color:var(--gray-800); }
  .item-sn { margin-top:7px; display:flex; gap:8px; align-items:center; }
  .item-sn input { padding:8px 10px; font-size:13px; }
  .item-sn label { font-size:10.5px; font-weight:700; color:var(--gray-600); text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.4px; white-space:nowrap; }
  .sn-help { font-size:12px; color:var(--gray-600); background:var(--gray-100); border-left:3px solid var(--blue-brand); padding:10px 13px; border-radius:0 6px 6px 0; line-height:1.6; margin-top:4px; }

  /* UNDERTAKING + SIGNATURE */
  .undertaking { font-size:12.8px; color:var(--gray-800); background:var(--gray-100); border:1px solid var(--gray-200); border-radius:8px; padding:14px 16px; line-height:1.65; margin-bottom:16px; }
  .sig-wrap { border:1.5px dashed var(--gray-300); border-radius:10px; background:#fff; position:relative; }
  .sig-canvas { width:100%; height:170px; display:block; border-radius:10px; touch-action:none; cursor:crosshair; }
  .sig-toggle { display:inline-flex; gap:0; border:1px solid var(--gray-300); border-radius:8px; overflow:hidden; margin-bottom:8px; }
  .sig-toggle .seg { background:#fff; border:none; padding:7px 16px; font-size:12.5px; font-weight:600; color:var(--gray-600); cursor:pointer; font-family:inherit; }
  .sig-toggle .seg + .seg { border-left:1px solid var(--gray-300); }
  .sig-toggle .seg.active { background:var(--blue-brand,#0a3d6b); color:#fff; }
  .sig-type-input { display:none; width:100%; height:170px; box-sizing:border-box; border:none; background:transparent; border-radius:10px; text-align:center; padding:0 16px; color:#0a3d6b; font-family:'Segoe Script','Brush Script MT','Snell Roundhand',cursive; font-size:46px; outline:none; }
  .sig-type-input::placeholder { font-family:inherit; color:var(--gray-300); font-size:24px; }
  .photo-add { display:inline-flex; align-items:center; gap:7px; background:#fff; border:1.5px solid var(--blue-brand,#0a3d6b); color:var(--blue-brand,#0a3d6b); border-radius:9px; padding:11px 18px; font-size:13.5px; font-weight:700; cursor:pointer; font-family:inherit; }
  .photo-grid { display:flex; flex-wrap:wrap; gap:10px; margin-top:12px; }
  .photo-thumb { position:relative; width:92px; height:92px; border-radius:8px; overflow:hidden; border:1px solid var(--gray-300); background:var(--gray-100); }
  .photo-thumb img { width:100%; height:100%; object-fit:cover; display:block; }
  .photo-thumb .rm { position:absolute; top:3px; right:3px; width:22px; height:22px; border:none; border-radius:50%; background:rgba(0,0,0,.6); color:#fff; font-size:14px; line-height:22px; text-align:center; cursor:pointer; padding:0; font-family:inherit; }
  .photo-count { font-size:11.5px; color:var(--gray-600); margin-top:8px; }
  .sig-bar { display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; padding:8px 12px; border-top:1px solid var(--gray-200); }
  .sig-hint { font-size:11.5px; color:var(--gray-600); }
  .sig-clear { background:#fff; border:1px solid var(--gray-300); color:var(--gray-600); border-radius:6px; padding:6px 12px; font-size:11.5px; font-weight:600; cursor:pointer; font-family:inherit; }

  /* ACTION BAR */
  .actions { position:sticky; bottom:0; background:#fff; border-top:1px solid var(--gray-200); padding:16px 28px; display:flex; gap:10px; flex-wrap:wrap; border-radius:0 0 10px 10px; }
  .btn { border:none; border-radius:9px; padding:13px 20px; font-size:14px; font-weight:700; cursor:pointer; font-family:inherit; display:inline-flex; align-items:center; gap:7px; }
  .btn-primary { background:var(--blue-brand); color:#fff; flex:1; min-width:200px; justify-content:center; }
  .btn-primary:hover { background:var(--blue-mid); }
  .btn-ghost { background:#fff; color:var(--blue-mid); border:1.5px solid var(--gray-300); }
  .btn-ghost:hover { border-color:var(--blue-brand); }
  .footnote { font-size:11.5px; color:var(--gray-600); padding:4px 28px 14px; }

  /* PRINT */
  @media print {
    body { background:#fff; padding:0; }
    .page { max-width:100%; padding:0; }
    .actions, .sig-clear, .footnote, .no-print { display:none !important; }
    .form-card, .site-header { box-shadow:none; border:none; border-radius:0; }
    .site-header { background:var(--blue-dark) !important; -webkit-print-color-adjust:exact; print-color-adjust:exact; }
    .item-row.checked { background:#eaf5ff !important; -webkit-print-color-adjust:exact; print-color-adjust:exact; }
    .sig-wrap { border:1px solid #999; }
    input, textarea { border:none !important; border-bottom:1px solid #888 !important; border-radius:0 !important; }
    .section { page-break-inside:avoid; }
  }
&lt;/style&gt;
&lt;/head&gt;
&lt;body&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;page&quot;&gt;
  &lt;div class=&quot;site-header&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;header-brand&quot;&gt;PulmOne USA Inc. &amp;middot; Service &amp;amp; Support&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;header-title&quot;&gt;MiniBox+&amp;trade; Replacement Request (RMA)&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;header-sub&quot;&gt;User Replacement Request Form &amp;mdash; fill in, sign, and send. No printing required.&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;div class=&quot;form-card&quot;&gt;

    &lt;!-- USER DETAILS --&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;section&quot;&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;sec-title&quot;&gt;User Details&lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;sec-hint&quot;&gt;Please complete the following so we have the most complete information possible.&lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;grid2&quot;&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;field&quot;&gt;&lt;label class=&quot;fld&quot;&gt;Date&lt;/label&gt;&lt;input type=&quot;date&quot; id=&quot;f-date&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;field&quot;&gt;&lt;label class=&quot;fld&quot;&gt;Full Name&lt;/label&gt;&lt;input type=&quot;text&quot; id=&quot;f-name&quot; placeholder=&quot;Type here&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;field&quot;&gt;&lt;label class=&quot;fld&quot;&gt;Job Role&lt;/label&gt;&lt;input type=&quot;text&quot; id=&quot;f-role&quot; placeholder=&quot;Type here&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;field&quot;&gt;&lt;label class=&quot;fld&quot;&gt;Institution / Clinic Name&lt;/label&gt;&lt;input type=&quot;text&quot; id=&quot;f-clinic&quot; placeholder=&quot;Type here&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;field&quot;&gt;&lt;label class=&quot;fld&quot;&gt;Email&lt;/label&gt;&lt;input type=&quot;email&quot; id=&quot;f-email&quot; placeholder=&quot;Type here&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;field&quot;&gt;&lt;label class=&quot;fld&quot;&gt;Cellphone / Phone&lt;/label&gt;&lt;input type=&quot;tel&quot; id=&quot;f-phone&quot; placeholder=&quot;Type here&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;field full&quot;&gt;&lt;label class=&quot;fld&quot;&gt;Full Address&lt;/label&gt;&lt;input type=&quot;text&quot; id=&quot;f-address&quot; placeholder=&quot;Type here&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;

    &lt;!-- REQUEST DETAILS --&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;section&quot;&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;sec-title&quot;&gt;Request Details&lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;sec-hint&quot;&gt;Please describe the issue you are having in your own words.&lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;field full&quot;&gt;&lt;textarea id=&quot;f-issue&quot; placeholder=&quot;Type here&quot;&gt;&lt;/textarea&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;

    &lt;!-- SUPPORTING EVIDENCE --&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;section&quot;&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;sec-title&quot;&gt;Supporting Evidence&lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;sec-hint&quot;&gt;Add photos of the issue &amp;mdash; they&amp;rsquo;re built right into the PDF that goes to PulmOne. Take a picture or pick from your library.&lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;label class=&quot;photo-add no-print&quot;&gt;
        &amp;#128247;&amp;nbsp; Add photos
        &lt;input type=&quot;file&quot; id=&quot;photoInput&quot; accept=&quot;image/*&quot; multiple style=&quot;display:none&quot;&gt;
      &lt;/label&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;photo-grid&quot; id=&quot;photoGrid&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;photo-count no-print&quot; id=&quot;photoCount&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;alert red&quot; style=&quot;margin-top:12px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Do not send ANY patient or patient health information whatsoever.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;alert&quot;&gt;Larger files (videos, log files) can be emailed to &lt;strong&gt;service@pulm-one.com&lt;/strong&gt; or faxed to &lt;strong&gt;844-785-6664&lt;/strong&gt;. Photos added above travel inside the same PDF when you tap &lt;em&gt;Send to PulmOne&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;

    &lt;!-- ITEM TO BE REPLACED --&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;section&quot;&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;sec-title&quot;&gt;Item to be Replaced&lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;sec-hint&quot;&gt;Check each item that needs replacing and enter its serial number.&lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;items&quot;&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;item-row&quot; id=&quot;row-0&quot;&gt;
          &lt;input type=&quot;checkbox&quot; class=&quot;chk&quot; id=&quot;it-0&quot; onchange=&quot;toggleItem(0)&quot;&gt;
          &lt;div class=&quot;item-main&quot;&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;item-name&quot;&gt;MiniBox+&amp;trade;&lt;/div&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;item-sn&quot;&gt;&lt;label for=&quot;sn-0&quot;&gt;S/N&lt;/label&gt;&lt;input type=&quot;text&quot; id=&quot;sn-0&quot; placeholder=&quot;Serial number&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
          &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;item-row&quot; id=&quot;row-1&quot;&gt;
          &lt;input type=&quot;checkbox&quot; class=&quot;chk&quot; id=&quot;it-1&quot; onchange=&quot;toggleItem(1)&quot;&gt;
          &lt;div class=&quot;item-main&quot;&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;item-name&quot;&gt;Hand-held Unit (HHU)&lt;/div&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;item-sn&quot;&gt;&lt;label for=&quot;sn-1&quot;&gt;S/N&lt;/label&gt;&lt;input type=&quot;text&quot; id=&quot;sn-1&quot; placeholder=&quot;Serial number&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
          &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;item-row&quot; id=&quot;row-2&quot;&gt;
          &lt;input type=&quot;checkbox&quot; class=&quot;chk&quot; id=&quot;it-2&quot; onchange=&quot;toggleItem(2)&quot;&gt;
          &lt;div class=&quot;item-main&quot;&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;item-name&quot;&gt;Control Unit &amp;mdash; Dell (Black Protective Case)&lt;/div&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;item-sn&quot;&gt;&lt;label for=&quot;sn-2&quot;&gt;S/N&lt;/label&gt;&lt;input type=&quot;text&quot; id=&quot;sn-2&quot; placeholder=&quot;Serial number&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
          &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;item-row&quot; id=&quot;row-3&quot;&gt;
          &lt;input type=&quot;checkbox&quot; class=&quot;chk&quot; id=&quot;it-3&quot; onchange=&quot;toggleItem(3)&quot;&gt;
          &lt;div class=&quot;item-main&quot;&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;item-name&quot;&gt;Other&lt;/div&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;item-sn&quot;&gt;&lt;label for=&quot;sn-3&quot;&gt;Describe&lt;/label&gt;&lt;input type=&quot;text&quot; id=&quot;sn-3&quot; placeholder=&quot;Type here&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
          &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;sn-help&quot;&gt;
        &lt;strong&gt;Finding serial numbers:&lt;/strong&gt; For the MiniBox+&amp;trade; or the HHU, tap &lt;strong&gt;Device Data&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;mdash; both appear on the upper right of the screen.
        The Control Unit S/N is on the back of the tablet, after removing its rubber cover.
      &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;

    &lt;!-- UNDERTAKING + SIGNATURE --&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;section&quot;&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;sec-title&quot;&gt;Undertaking &amp;amp; Signature&lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;undertaking&quot;&gt;
        I undertake to fully collaborate with a PulmOne USA Inc. representative to ship back the replaced item (at PulmOne&amp;rsquo;s expense), or otherwise be subject to triple penalties of this item&amp;rsquo;s cost to PulmOne.
      &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;grid2&quot; style=&quot;margin-bottom:14px;&quot;&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;field&quot;&gt;&lt;label class=&quot;fld&quot;&gt;Signed By (Name)&lt;/label&gt;&lt;input type=&quot;text&quot; id=&quot;f-signname&quot; placeholder=&quot;Type here&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;field&quot;&gt;&lt;label class=&quot;fld&quot;&gt;Date Signed&lt;/label&gt;&lt;input type=&quot;date&quot; id=&quot;f-sigdate&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;label class=&quot;fld&quot; style=&quot;display:block; margin-bottom:6px;&quot;&gt;Signature&lt;/label&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;sig-toggle no-print&quot;&gt;
        &lt;button type=&quot;button&quot; id=&quot;modeDraw&quot; class=&quot;seg active&quot; onclick=&quot;setSigMode('draw')&quot;&gt;&amp;#9997;&amp;nbsp; Draw&lt;/button&gt;
        &lt;button type=&quot;button&quot; id=&quot;modeType&quot; class=&quot;seg&quot; onclick=&quot;setSigMode('type')&quot;&gt;&amp;#9000;&amp;nbsp; Type&lt;/button&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;sig-wrap&quot;&gt;
        &lt;canvas id=&quot;sigCanvas&quot; class=&quot;sig-canvas&quot;&gt;&lt;/canvas&gt;
        &lt;input type=&quot;text&quot; id=&quot;sigType&quot; class=&quot;sig-type-input&quot; placeholder=&quot;Type your name to sign&quot; autocomplete=&quot;off&quot;&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;sig-bar&quot;&gt;
          &lt;span class=&quot;sig-hint&quot; id=&quot;sigHint&quot;&gt;Sign with your finger, stylus, or mouse.&lt;/span&gt;
          &lt;button class=&quot;sig-clear&quot; onclick=&quot;clearSig()&quot;&gt;Clear signature&lt;/button&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;

    &lt;!-- ACTIONS --&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;actions no-print&quot;&gt;
      &lt;button class=&quot;btn btn-primary&quot; onclick=&quot;sendToPulmOne()&quot;&gt;&amp;#9993;&amp;nbsp; Send to PulmOne&lt;/button&gt;
      &lt;button class=&quot;btn btn-ghost&quot; onclick=&quot;window.print()&quot;&gt;&amp;#128424;&amp;nbsp; Save / Print PDF&lt;/button&gt;
      &lt;button class=&quot;btn btn-ghost&quot; onclick=&quot;resetAll()&quot;&gt;&amp;#10227;&amp;nbsp; Reset&lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;footnote no-print&quot;&gt;
      Goes to &lt;strong&gt;service@pulm-one.com&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;middot; fax 844-785-6664. On iPad/iPhone, &lt;em&gt;Send to PulmOne&lt;/em&gt; opens your share sheet with the completed form attached as a PDF. On a computer it saves the PDF and opens a pre-addressed email.
    &lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;script&gt;
(function(){
  var SERVICE_EMAIL = 'service@pulm-one.com';

  function $(id){ return document.getElementById(id); }
  function todayISO(){ var d=new Date(); return d.getFullYear()+'-'+String(d.getMonth()+1).padStart(2,'0')+'-'+String(d.getDate()).padStart(2,'0'); }

  /* ---------- Item rows ---------- */
  window.toggleItem=function(i){
    var row=$('row-'+i); var on=$('it-'+i).checked;
    row.classList.toggle('checked', on);
  };

  /* ---------- Signature pad ---------- */
  var canvas, ctx, drawing=false, hasSig=false, last=null, ratio=1, sigMode='draw', typeInput;
  function sizeCanvas(){
    var rect=canvas.getBoundingClientRect();
    var w=rect.width||canvas.offsetWidth||520, h=rect.height||170;
    ratio=window.devicePixelRatio||1;
    canvas.width=Math.round(w*ratio); canvas.height=Math.round(h*ratio);
    ctx=canvas.getContext('2d');
    ctx.setTransform(ratio,0,0,ratio,0,0);
    ctx.lineWidth=2.4; ctx.lineCap='round'; ctx.lineJoin='round'; ctx.strokeStyle='#0a3d6b';
  }
  function cssW(){ return canvas.width/ratio; }
  function cssH(){ return canvas.height/ratio; }
  function initSig(){
    canvas=$('sigCanvas'); if(!canvas) return;
    typeInput=$('sigType');
    sizeCanvas();
    if(canvas.width&lt;10){ setTimeout(sizeCanvas,120); }
    function pos(e){
      var r=canvas.getBoundingClientRect();
      return { x:e.clientX-r.left, y:e.clientY-r.top };
    }
    function start(e){
      if(sigMode!=='draw') return;
      e.preventDefault();
      drawing=true; last=pos(e);
      try{ canvas.setPointerCapture(e.pointerId); }catch(_){}
    }
    function move(e){
      if(!drawing||sigMode!=='draw') return;
      e.preventDefault();
      var p=pos(e);
      ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(last.x,last.y); ctx.lineTo(p.x,p.y); ctx.stroke();
      last=p; hasSig=true;
    }
    function end(e){ drawing=false; try{ canvas.releasePointerCapture(e.pointerId); }catch(_){} }
    if(window.PointerEvent){
      canvas.addEventListener('pointerdown',start);
      canvas.addEventListener('pointermove',move);
      canvas.addEventListener('pointerup',end);
      canvas.addEventListener('pointercancel',end);
      canvas.addEventListener('pointerleave',function(e){ if(drawing) end(e); });
    } else {
      canvas.addEventListener('mousedown',start);
      canvas.addEventListener('mousemove',move);
      window.addEventListener('mouseup',end);
      canvas.addEventListener('touchstart',function(e){ var t=e.touches[0]; start({clientX:t.clientX,clientY:t.clientY,preventDefault:function(){e.preventDefault();}}); },{passive:false});
      canvas.addEventListener('touchmove',function(e){ var t=e.touches[0]; move({clientX:t.clientX,clientY:t.clientY,preventDefault:function(){e.preventDefault();}}); },{passive:false});
      canvas.addEventListener('touchend',end);
    }
    if(typeInput){ typeInput.addEventListener('input',renderTypedSig); }
  }
  function renderTypedSig(){
    if(!ctx) return;
    ctx.clearRect(0,0,cssW(),cssH());
    var txt=(typeInput&amp;&amp;typeInput.value||'').trim();
    if(!txt){ hasSig=false; return; }
    var fs=46, max=cssW()-32;
    ctx.fillStyle='#0a3d6b';
    ctx.textAlign='center'; ctx.textBaseline='middle';
    ctx.font=&quot;46px 'Segoe Script','Brush Script MT','Snell Roundhand',cursive&quot;;
    while(ctx.measureText(txt).width&gt;max &amp;&amp; fs&gt;16){ fs-=2; ctx.font=fs+&quot;px 'Segoe Script','Brush Script MT','Snell Roundhand',cursive&quot;; }
    ctx.fillText(txt, cssW()/2, cssH()/2);
    hasSig=true;
  }
  window.setSigMode=function(m){
    sigMode=m;
    var draw=$('modeDraw'), type=$('modeType'), hint=$('sigHint');
    draw.classList.toggle('active', m==='draw');
    type.classList.toggle('active', m==='type');
    if(m==='type'){
      canvas.style.display='none';
      typeInput.style.display='block';
      hint.textContent='Type your name — it appears in cursive as your signature.';
      renderTypedSig();
      typeInput.focus();
    } else {
      typeInput.style.display='none';
      canvas.style.display='block';
      hint.textContent='Sign with your finger, stylus, or mouse.';
      sizeCanvas();
    }
  };
  window.clearSig=function(){
    if(ctx){ ctx.clearRect(0,0,canvas.width,canvas.height); }
    if(typeInput){ typeInput.value=''; }
    hasSig=false;
  };
  function commitSig(){ if(sigMode==='type') renderTypedSig(); }

  /* ---------- Photos (downscaled, embedded into the PDF) ---------- */
  var photos=[];
  window.addPhotos=function(fileList){
    var files=Array.prototype.slice.call(fileList||[]);
    files.forEach(function(file){
      if(!/^image\//.test(file.type)) return;
      var reader=new FileReader();
      reader.onload=function(ev){
        var im=new Image();
        im.onload=function(){
          var maxDim=1400;
          var w=im.naturalWidth||im.width, h=im.naturalHeight||im.height;
          var sc=Math.min(1, maxDim/Math.max(w,h));
          var cw=Math.max(1,Math.round(w*sc)), ch=Math.max(1,Math.round(h*sc));
          var c=document.createElement('canvas'); c.width=cw; c.height=ch;
          c.getContext('2d').drawImage(im,0,0,cw,ch);
          var data;
          try{ data=c.toDataURL('image/jpeg',0.82); }catch(e){ data=ev.target.result; }
          photos.push({ data:data, w:cw, h:ch });
          renderThumbs();
        };
        im.onerror=function(){};
        im.src=ev.target.result;
      };
      reader.readAsDataURL(file);
    });
  };
  function renderThumbs(){
    var grid=$('photoGrid'), cnt=$('photoCount'); if(!grid) return;
    grid.innerHTML='';
    photos.forEach(function(ph,i){
      var d=document.createElement('div'); d.className='photo-thumb';
      var img=document.createElement('img'); img.src=ph.data; d.appendChild(img);
      var b=document.createElement('button'); b.className='rm no-print'; b.type='button';
      b.innerHTML='&amp;times;'; b.title='Remove'; b.onclick=function(){ removePhoto(i); };
      d.appendChild(b); grid.appendChild(d);
    });
    if(cnt){ cnt.textContent = photos.length ? (photos.length+' photo'+(photos.length&gt;1?'s':'')+' will be added to the PDF.') : ''; }
  }
  window.removePhoto=function(i){ photos.splice(i,1); renderThumbs(); };

  /* ---------- Gather form data ---------- */
  function gather(){
    var items=[];
    [['MiniBox+ (TM)','sn-0','it-0'],['Hand-held Unit (HHU)','sn-1','it-1'],
     ['Control Unit - Dell (Black Protective Case)','sn-2','it-2'],['Other','sn-3','it-3']]
      .forEach(function(t){ if($(t[2]).checked){ items.push({ name:t[0], sn:$(t[1]).value.trim() }); } });
    return {
      date:$('f-date').value, name:$('f-name').value.trim(), role:$('f-role').value.trim(),
      clinic:$('f-clinic').value.trim(), email:$('f-email').value.trim(), phone:$('f-phone').value.trim(),
      address:$('f-address').value.trim(), issue:$('f-issue').value.trim(),
      items:items, signName:$('f-signname').value.trim(), sigDate:$('f-sigdate').value,
      photos:photos.slice()
    };
  }
  function emailBody(d){
    var L=[];
    L.push('MiniBox+ Replacement Request (RMA)');
    L.push('');
    L.push('USER DETAILS');
    L.push('Date: '+(d.date||''));
    L.push('Full name: '+d.name);
    L.push('Job role: '+d.role);
    L.push('Institution / Clinic: '+d.clinic);
    L.push('Email: '+d.email);
    L.push('Phone: '+d.phone);
    L.push('Address: '+d.address);
    L.push('');
    L.push('ISSUE DESCRIPTION');
    L.push(d.issue||'(see attached)');
    L.push('');
    L.push('ITEM(S) TO BE REPLACED');
    if(d.items.length){ d.items.forEach(function(it){ L.push('- '+it.name+(it.sn?('  S/N: '+it.sn):'  S/N: (not provided)')); }); }
    else { L.push('(none checked)'); }
    L.push('');
    if(d.photos&amp;&amp;d.photos.length){ L.push('Photos: '+d.photos.length+' attached inside the PDF.'); L.push(''); }
    L.push('Signed by: '+(d.signName||'(see attached signature)')+'   Date: '+(d.sigDate||''));
    L.push('');
    L.push('Undertaking: I undertake to fully collaborate with a PulmOne USA Inc. representative to ship back the replaced item (at PulmOne expense), or otherwise be subject to triple penalties of this item cost to PulmOne.');
    L.push('');
    L.push('Reminder: do not send any patient or patient health information.');
    return L.join('\n');
  }
  function subject(d){
    var who=d.clinic||d.name||'MiniBox+ Customer';
    return 'MiniBox+ Replacement Request (RMA) - '+who;
  }

  /* ---------- PDF (lazy-load jsPDF from CDN) ---------- */
  function loadJsPDF(cb){
    if(window.jspdf&amp;&amp;window.jspdf.jsPDF){ cb(window.jspdf.jsPDF); return; }
    var s=document.createElement('script');
    s.src='https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/jspdf/2.5.1/jspdf.umd.min.js';
    s.onload=function(){ cb(window.jspdf&amp;&amp;window.jspdf.jsPDF); };
    s.onerror=function(){ cb(null); };
    document.head.appendChild(s);
  }
  function buildPDF(JsPDF,d){
    var doc=new JsPDF({unit:'pt',format:'letter'});
    var W=612, x=48, y=56, line=16;
    doc.setFillColor(10,61,107); doc.rect(0,0,W,70,'F');
    doc.setTextColor(255,255,255); doc.setFont('helvetica','bold'); doc.setFontSize(16);
    doc.text('MiniBox+ Replacement Request (RMA)',x,40);
    doc.setFontSize(9); doc.setFont('helvetica','normal');
    doc.text('PulmOne USA Inc.  -  Service &amp; Support',x,56);
    doc.setTextColor(26,39,51); y=98;
    function h(t){ doc.setFont('helvetica','bold'); doc.setFontSize(11); doc.setTextColor(10,61,107); doc.text(t,x,y); y+=line+2; doc.setTextColor(26,39,51); }
    function p(lbl,val){ doc.setFont('helvetica','bold'); doc.setFontSize(9.5); doc.text(lbl,x,y);
      doc.setFont('helvetica','normal'); var lines=doc.splitTextToSize(String(val||'-'),W-x-x-90);
      doc.text(lines,x+96,y); y+=Math.max(line,lines.length*13); }
    h('User Details');
    p('Date',d.date); p('Full name',d.name); p('Job role',d.role); p('Clinic',d.clinic);
    p('Email',d.email); p('Phone',d.phone); p('Address',d.address); y+=6;
    h('Issue Description');
    doc.setFont('helvetica','normal'); doc.setFontSize(10);
    var il=doc.splitTextToSize(d.issue||'(see attached evidence)',W-x-x); doc.text(il,x,y); y+=il.length*13+8;
    h('Item(s) to be Replaced');
    doc.setFontSize(10);
    if(d.items.length){ d.items.forEach(function(it){ doc.setFont('helvetica','normal');
      doc.text('[X] '+it.name+'   S/N: '+(it.sn||'(not provided)'),x,y); y+=line; }); }
    else { doc.text('(none checked)',x,y); y+=line; }
    y+=6;
    h('Undertaking');
    doc.setFont('helvetica','normal'); doc.setFontSize(9);
    var ut=doc.splitTextToSize('I undertake to fully collaborate with a PulmOne USA Inc. representative to ship back the replaced item (at PulmOne expense), or otherwise be subject to triple penalties of this item cost to PulmOne.',W-x-x);
    doc.text(ut,x,y); y+=ut.length*12+12;
    doc.setFont('helvetica','bold'); doc.setFontSize(9.5);
    doc.text('Signed by: '+(d.signName||'____________________')+'        Date: '+(d.sigDate||'__________'),x,y); y+=10;
    if(hasSig){ try{ var img=canvas.toDataURL('image/png');
      doc.addImage(img,'PNG',x,y,180,60); y+=64; }catch(e){} }
    doc.setFont('helvetica','italic'); doc.setFontSize(8); doc.setTextColor(150,40,30);
    doc.text('Do not send any patient or patient health information.',x,y+8);
    if(d.photos &amp;&amp; d.photos.length){
      d.photos.forEach(function(ph,i){
        doc.addPage();
        doc.setFillColor(10,61,107); doc.rect(0,0,W,50,'F');
        doc.setTextColor(255,255,255); doc.setFont('helvetica','bold'); doc.setFontSize(12);
        doc.text('Supporting Photo '+(i+1)+' of '+d.photos.length,x,32);
        doc.setTextColor(26,39,51);
        var maxW=W-72, maxH=792-90, ox=36, oy=70;
        var scale=Math.min(maxW/ph.w, maxH/ph.h);
        var wPt=ph.w*scale, hPt=ph.h*scale, px=ox+(maxW-wPt)/2;
        try{ doc.addImage(ph.data,'JPEG',px,oy,wPt,hPt); }catch(e){}
      });
    }
    return doc;
  }
  function fileName(d){
    var who=(d.clinic||d.name||'Customer').replace(/[^a-z0-9]+/gi,'_').replace(/^_|_$/g,'');
    return 'MiniBox_RMA_'+who+'_'+(d.date||todayISO())+'.pdf';
  }

  /* ---------- Send ---------- */
  window.sendToPulmOne=function(){
    commitSig();
    var d=gather();
    if(!d.name &amp;&amp; !d.clinic){ alert('Add at least the customer name or clinic before sending.'); return; }
    if(!d.items.length){ if(!confirm('No item is checked as needing replacement. Send anyway?')) return; }
    if(!hasSig &amp;&amp; !d.signName){ if(!confirm('No signature or signer name yet. Send anyway?')) return; }
    var subj=subject(d), body=emailBody(d), fn=fileName(d);
    loadJsPDF(function(JsPDF){
      if(JsPDF){
        try{
          var doc=buildPDF(JsPDF,d);
          var blob=doc.output('blob');
          var file=new File([blob],fn,{type:'application/pdf'});
          if(navigator.canShare &amp;&amp; navigator.canShare({files:[file]})){
            navigator.share({ files:[file], title:subj, text:body })
              .catch(function(){ fallbackEmail(doc,fn,subj,body,d); });
            return;
          }
          fallbackEmail(doc,fn,subj,body,d); return;
        }catch(e){ /* fall through */ }
      }
      // No PDF available: print + mailto
      mailtoOnly(subj,body,d);
      setTimeout(function(){ window.print(); },400);
    });
  };
  function fallbackEmail(doc,fn,subj,body,d){
    try{ doc.save(fn); }catch(e){}
    mailtoOnly(subj,body+'\n\n[The completed form PDF was just saved to your device — please attach it: '+fn+']',d);
  }
  function mailtoOnly(subj,body,d){
    var cc=d.email?('&amp;cc='+encodeURIComponent(d.email)):'';
    var href='mailto:'+SERVICE_EMAIL+'?subject='+encodeURIComponent(subj)+cc+'&amp;body='+encodeURIComponent(body);
    window.location.href=href;
  }

  window.resetAll=function(){
    if(!confirm('Clear the whole form?')) return;
    document.querySelectorAll('input[type=text],input[type=email],input[type=tel]').forEach(function(i){ i.value=''; });
    $('f-issue').value='';
    for(var k=0;k&lt;4;k++){ $('it-'+k).checked=false; toggleItem(k); }
    clearSig();
    photos=[]; renderThumbs();
    setSigMode('draw');
    $('f-date').value=todayISO(); $('f-sigdate').value=todayISO();
  };

  /* ---------- Init ---------- */
  function init(){
    $('f-date').value=todayISO();
    $('f-sigdate').value=todayISO();
    initSig();
    var pin=$('photoInput');
    if(pin){ pin.addEventListener('change',function(){ addPhotos(this.files); this.value=''; }); }
  }
  if(document.readyState==='loading') document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded',init); else init();
  window.addEventListener('resize',function(){ /* keep signature; no re-init to avoid wiping */ });
})();
&lt;/script&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;
"></iframe>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ==================== INSTALLATION COMPLETION FORM (embedded v3.8) ==================== -->
    <div class="form-card" style="margin-bottom: 28px;">
      <div class="form-card-header" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0a3d6b, #0e6abf);">
        <div>
          <div class="form-card-title">&#128736; Installation Completion Form (DHR008)</div>
          <div class="form-card-sub">Fill in &middot; tap Yes/No &middot; sign &middot; Save as PDF &mdash; Rev 4.0</div>
        </div>
        <div style="display:flex; gap:8px; align-items:center; flex-wrap:wrap;">
          <span style="font-size:11px; color:rgba(255,255,255,0.7); letter-spacing:0.06em;">EMBEDDED</span>
          <button onclick="(function(f){var r=f.requestFullscreen||f.webkitRequestFullscreen||f.mozRequestFullScreen||f.msRequestFullscreen;if(r)r.call(f);})(document.getElementById('icf-iframe'))" style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.15); border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.3); color:#fff; border-radius:6px; padding:7px 14px; font-family:'Inter',sans-serif; font-size:11.5px; font-weight:600; cursor:pointer;">&#9974; Fullscreen</button>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="form-body" style="padding: 0;">
        <div style="background:#f1f5f9; padding:10px 18px; font-size:12px; color:#475569; border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">
          &#9432; Service-specialist sign-off for a MiniBox+ install. Type the details, tap <strong>Yes</strong> or <strong>No</strong> on each line, type signatures, then <strong>Save as PDF / Print</strong>. Your entries auto-save on this device.
        </div>
        <iframe id="icf-iframe" allow="fullscreen; clipboard-write"
          style="width:100%; border:0; height:5200px; display:block; background:#eef2f7;"
          srcdoc="&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
&lt;html lang=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
&lt;head&gt;
&lt;meta charset=&quot;UTF-8&quot;&gt;
&lt;meta name=&quot;viewport&quot; content=&quot;width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0&quot;&gt;
&lt;title&gt;PulmOne Installation Completion Form — DHR008 Rev 4.0&lt;/title&gt;
&lt;style&gt;
  @import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700;800&amp;display=swap');
  @import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Dancing+Script:wght@600;700&amp;display=swap');
  :root{
    --blue-dark:#0a3d6b; --blue-mid:#0c5299; --blue-brand:#0e6abf; --blue-light:#d6eaf8;
    --green:#27ae60; --green-bg:#e7f7ee; --red:#c0392b; --red-bg:#fdecea;
    --gray-100:#f4f6f9; --gray-200:#e8ecf0; --gray-300:#c8d0d8; --gray-500:#8a96a3;
    --gray-600:#5a6a7a; --gray-800:#1e2d3d; --text:#1a2733;
  }
  *{box-sizing:border-box;}
  html,body{margin:0;padding:0;}
  body{font-family:'Inter',sans-serif; background:#eef2f7; color:var(--text); -webkit-text-size-adjust:100%;}
  .wrap{max-width:920px; margin:0 auto; padding:0 14px 80px;}

  /* Header */
  .topbar{background:#fff; color:var(--text); padding:16px 20px; border-bottom:3px solid var(--blue-dark);}
  .topbar-inner{max-width:920px; margin:0 auto; display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:space-between; gap:16px; flex-wrap:wrap;}
  .brand-logo-img{height:58px; width:auto; display:block; margin-left:-6px;}
  .head-right{text-align:right;}
  .head-title{font-size:20px; font-weight:700; line-height:1.15; color:var(--blue-dark);}
  .head-sub{font-size:12px; color:var(--gray-600); margin-top:3px; letter-spacing:0.04em;}
  .head-tag{font-size:11px; color:var(--gray-500); font-style:italic; margin-top:5px; letter-spacing:0.02em;}

  /* Action bar */
  .actions{position:static; z-index:20; background:#eef2f7; padding:12px 0 10px; display:flex; gap:10px; justify-content:flex-end; flex-wrap:wrap; border-bottom:1px solid var(--gray-200); margin-bottom:6px;}
  .btn{font-family:inherit; font-size:14px; font-weight:600; padding:11px 18px; border-radius:9px; border:1.5px solid; cursor:pointer; min-height:44px;}
  .btn-primary{background:var(--blue-brand); color:#fff; border-color:var(--blue-brand);}
  .btn-primary:hover{background:var(--blue-mid);}
  .btn-ghost{background:#fff; color:var(--gray-600); border-color:var(--gray-300);}
  .btn-ghost:hover{background:var(--gray-100);}
  .save-note{font-size:12px; color:var(--gray-500); align-self:center; margin-right:auto;}

  /* Cards */
  .card{background:#fff; border:1px solid var(--gray-200); border-radius:12px; margin:14px 0; overflow:hidden; box-shadow:0 1px 2px rgba(16,42,67,0.04);}
  .card-head{background:var(--blue-dark); color:#fff; padding:11px 16px; font-size:15px; font-weight:700;}
  .card-head .sub{display:block; font-size:11px; font-weight:500; color:#a8d0ee; margin-top:2px;}
  .card-body{padding:14px 16px;}

  /* Fields */
  .grid2{display:grid; grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr; gap:12px;}
  .grid3{display:grid; grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr 1fr; gap:12px;}
  @media(max-width:640px){.grid2,.grid3{grid-template-columns:1fr;}}
  .field{display:flex; flex-direction:column; gap:5px;}
  .field label{font-size:11px; font-weight:700; color:var(--blue-mid); text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.04em;}
  .inp{font-family:inherit; font-size:15px; padding:11px 12px; border:1.5px solid var(--gray-300); border-radius:9px; background:#fff; width:100%; min-height:44px;}
  .inp:focus{outline:none; border-color:var(--blue-brand); box-shadow:0 0 0 3px rgba(14,106,191,0.14);}
  textarea.inp{min-height:90px; resize:vertical;}
  .inp.sig{font-family:'Dancing Script', cursive; font-size:24px; font-weight:700; color:var(--blue-dark); padding-top:6px;}

  /* Checklist */
  .clist-head{display:grid; grid-template-columns:30px 1fr 150px 190px; gap:10px; padding:6px 4px; font-size:10px; font-weight:700; color:var(--gray-500); text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.05em; border-bottom:2px solid var(--gray-200);}
  .clist-head .c-yn{text-align:center;}
  .item{display:grid; grid-template-columns:30px 1fr 150px 190px; gap:10px; align-items:center; padding:9px 4px; border-bottom:1px solid var(--gray-200);}
  .item:last-child{border-bottom:none;}
  .item .num{font-weight:700; color:var(--blue-dark); font-size:13px;}
  .item .lbl{font-size:14px; line-height:1.3;}
  .item.sub .lbl{color:var(--gray-600); padding-left:10px; font-size:13px;}
  .item .cmt{font-family:inherit; font-size:13px; padding:8px 10px; border:1.5px solid var(--gray-300); border-radius:8px; min-height:38px;}
  .item .cmt:focus{outline:none; border-color:var(--blue-brand);}
  @media(max-width:640px){
    .clist-head{display:none;}
    .item{grid-template-columns:24px 1fr; grid-template-areas:&quot;num lbl&quot; &quot;. yn&quot; &quot;. cmt&quot;; gap:8px;}
    .item .num{grid-area:num;} .item .lbl{grid-area:lbl;}
    .item .yn{grid-area:yn; justify-self:start;} .item .cmt{grid-area:cmt;}
  }

  /* Yes/No toggle */
  .yn{display:inline-flex; gap:6px; justify-content:center;}
  .yn-btn{font-family:inherit; font-size:14px; font-weight:700; padding:9px 0; width:62px; border-radius:9px; border:1.5px solid var(--gray-300); background:#fff; color:var(--gray-600); cursor:pointer; min-height:42px;}
  .yn-btn.yes.active{background:var(--green); border-color:var(--green); color:#fff;}
  .yn-btn.no.active{background:var(--red); border-color:var(--red); color:#fff;}
  .yn-btn:active{transform:scale(0.97);}

  /* Staff contact table */
  .staff-row{display:grid; grid-template-columns:1.2fr 1fr 1fr 1fr; gap:8px; padding:7px 0; align-items:center; border-bottom:1px solid var(--gray-200);}
  .staff-row .role{font-size:13px; font-weight:600; color:var(--gray-800);}
  .staff-row .inp{font-size:13px; padding:8px 10px; min-height:38px;}
  .staff-head{display:grid; grid-template-columns:1.2fr 1fr 1fr 1fr; gap:8px; font-size:12px; font-weight:700; color:var(--blue-dark); text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.03em; padding-bottom:6px; border-bottom:2px solid var(--blue-light);}
  @media(max-width:640px){
    .staff-head{display:none;}
    .staff-row{grid-template-columns:1fr; gap:5px; padding:10px 0;}
    .staff-row .role{font-weight:700; color:var(--blue-dark);}
  }

  /* VII grid */
  .gwrap{overflow-x:auto; -webkit-overflow-scrolling:touch;}
  table.grid{border-collapse:collapse; width:100%; min-width:640px; font-size:12px;}
  table.grid th, table.grid td{border:1px solid var(--gray-200); padding:4px; text-align:center;}
  table.grid th.item-h, table.grid td.item-c{text-align:left; min-width:170px; font-weight:600;}
  table.grid thead th{background:var(--blue-dark); color:#fff; font-weight:600; font-size:11px;}
  table.grid thead th input{width:74px; font-size:11px; padding:5px 4px; border:1px solid #2c6094; border-radius:5px; background:#0f4d83; color:#fff;}
  table.grid thead th input::placeholder{color:#9fc4e6;}
  table.grid tbody tr:nth-child(even){background:var(--gray-100);}
  .cyc{font-family:inherit; font-weight:800; font-size:14px; width:40px; height:36px; border-radius:7px; border:1.5px solid var(--gray-300); background:#fff; color:var(--gray-400); cursor:pointer;}
  .cyc[data-v=&quot;Y&quot;]{background:var(--green-bg); border-color:var(--green); color:var(--green);}
  .cyc[data-v=&quot;N&quot;]{background:var(--red-bg); border-color:var(--red); color:var(--red);}
  .grid-init{width:78px; font-size:11px; padding:5px; border:1.5px solid var(--gray-300); border-radius:6px;}
  .hint{font-size:12px; color:var(--gray-500); margin:0 0 8px;}

  /* attestation */
  .attest{background:var(--blue-light); border:1px solid #bcdcf3; border-radius:10px; padding:14px 16px; font-size:13px; line-height:1.55; color:var(--gray-800);}
  .attest b{color:var(--blue-dark);}
  .attest p{margin:0 0 9px;}
  .attest p:last-child{margin-bottom:0;}

  .sigrow{display:grid; grid-template-columns:2fr 1fr; gap:12px;}
  @media(max-width:640px){.sigrow{grid-template-columns:1fr;}}

  /* PRINT */
  @media print{
    @page{margin:12mm;}
    body{background:#fff;}
    .actions,.save-note,.hint{display:none !important;}
    .wrap{max-width:none; padding:0;}
    .topbar{background:#fff !important; color:#000 !important; padding:0 0 8px; border-bottom:2px solid var(--blue-dark);}
    .brand-logo-img{background:#fff !important; padding:0; -webkit-print-color-adjust:exact; print-color-adjust:exact;} .head-title{color:#000;} .head-sub{color:#555 !important;}
    .card{border:1px solid #bbb; box-shadow:none; margin:8px 0; page-break-inside:avoid;}
    .card-head{background:var(--blue-dark) !important; -webkit-print-color-adjust:exact; print-color-adjust:exact;}
    .inp,.cmt,.grid-init{border:none; border-bottom:1px solid #999; border-radius:0; box-shadow:none !important; padding-left:2px;}
    .inp::placeholder,.cmt::placeholder,.grid-init::placeholder{color:transparent !important;}
    input[type=date]::-webkit-calendar-picker-indicator{display:none;}
    .yn-btn{width:auto; padding:2px 10px; min-height:0; -webkit-print-color-adjust:exact; print-color-adjust:exact;}
    .yn-btn:not(.active){opacity:0.30; color:#888;}
    .cyc{-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact; print-color-adjust:exact; width:auto; height:auto; padding:2px 6px;}
    table.grid thead th input{background:#0f4d83 !important; -webkit-print-color-adjust:exact; print-color-adjust:exact;}
  }
&lt;/style&gt;
&lt;/head&gt;
&lt;body&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;topbar&quot;&gt;
  &lt;div class=&quot;topbar-inner&quot;&gt;
    &lt;img class=&quot;brand-logo-img&quot; src=&quot;data:image/jpeg;base64,&quot; alt=&quot;PulmOne&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;head-right&quot;&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;head-title&quot;&gt;Installation Completion Form&lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;head-sub&quot;&gt;Document no. DHR008 &amp;nbsp;•&amp;nbsp; Revision 4.0&lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;head-tag&quot;&gt;Easy. Accurate. Available. Lung Function Testing&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;wrap&quot;&gt;

  &lt;div class=&quot;actions&quot;&gt;
    &lt;span class=&quot;save-note&quot; id=&quot;saveNote&quot;&gt;Auto-saving your progress on this device&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;button class=&quot;btn btn-ghost&quot; onclick=&quot;clearForm()&quot;&gt;&amp;#8635; Clear Form&lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;button class=&quot;btn btn-primary&quot; onclick=&quot;window.print()&quot;&gt;&amp;#128190; Save as PDF / Print&lt;/button&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;!-- Install report meta --&gt;
  &lt;div class=&quot;card&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;card-head&quot;&gt;PulmOne Installation Report&lt;span class=&quot;sub&quot;&gt;To be filled by a certified PulmOne Service Specialist&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;card-body&quot;&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;grid3&quot;&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;field&quot;&gt;&lt;label&gt;PO Number&lt;/label&gt;&lt;input class=&quot;inp&quot; id=&quot;po_number&quot; placeholder=&quot;PO #&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;field&quot;&gt;&lt;label&gt;Installation Date&lt;/label&gt;&lt;input type=&quot;date&quot; class=&quot;inp&quot; id=&quot;install_date&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;field&quot;&gt;&lt;label&gt;Installer Name&lt;/label&gt;&lt;input class=&quot;inp&quot; id=&quot;installer_name&quot; placeholder=&quot;Your name&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;!-- I Product Details --&gt;
  &lt;div class=&quot;card&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;card-head&quot;&gt;I. &amp;nbsp;Product Details&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;card-body&quot;&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;grid2&quot;&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;field&quot;&gt;&lt;label&gt;Product Name&lt;/label&gt;&lt;input class=&quot;inp&quot; id=&quot;product_name&quot; placeholder=&quot;e.g. MiniBox Plus&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;field&quot;&gt;&lt;label&gt;Device S/N&lt;/label&gt;&lt;input class=&quot;inp&quot; id=&quot;device_sn&quot; placeholder=&quot;Device serial number&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;field&quot;&gt;&lt;label&gt;Tablet S/N&lt;/label&gt;&lt;input class=&quot;inp&quot; id=&quot;tablet_sn&quot; placeholder=&quot;Tablet serial number&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;field&quot;&gt;&lt;label&gt;HHU S/N&lt;/label&gt;&lt;input class=&quot;inp&quot; id=&quot;hhu_sn&quot; placeholder=&quot;Handheld unit serial number&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;!-- II Customer Details --&gt;
  &lt;div class=&quot;card&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;card-head&quot;&gt;II. &amp;nbsp;Customer Details&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;card-body&quot;&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;grid2&quot; style=&quot;margin-bottom:12px;&quot;&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;field&quot;&gt;&lt;label&gt;Name&lt;/label&gt;&lt;input class=&quot;inp&quot; id=&quot;cust_name&quot; placeholder=&quot;Practice / facility name&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;field&quot;&gt;&lt;label&gt;Address&lt;/label&gt;&lt;input class=&quot;inp&quot; id=&quot;cust_address&quot; placeholder=&quot;Street address&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;field&quot;&gt;&lt;label&gt;City / State / ZIP&lt;/label&gt;&lt;input class=&quot;inp&quot; id=&quot;cust_city&quot; placeholder=&quot;City, ST ZIP&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;field&quot;&gt;&lt;label&gt;Phone&lt;/label&gt;&lt;input class=&quot;inp&quot; id=&quot;cust_phone&quot; placeholder=&quot;Phone&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;field&quot;&gt;&lt;label&gt;Email&lt;/label&gt;&lt;input class=&quot;inp&quot; id=&quot;cust_email&quot; placeholder=&quot;Email&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;

      &lt;div class=&quot;staff-head&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;Customer's Staff&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Name + Credentials&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Phone / Cell&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Email&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div id=&quot;staffRows&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;!-- III Received Items --&gt;
  &lt;div class=&quot;card&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;card-head&quot;&gt;III. &amp;nbsp;Received Items&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;card-body&quot;&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;clist-head&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;#&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Item&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;c-yn&quot;&gt;Yes / No&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Comments&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div id=&quot;recvList&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;!-- IV Acceptance Tests --&gt;
  &lt;div class=&quot;card&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;card-head&quot;&gt;IV. &amp;nbsp;Acceptance Tests&lt;span class=&quot;sub&quot;&gt;To be demonstrated and performed by PulmOne's Service Specialist&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;card-body&quot;&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;clist-head&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;#&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Test&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;c-yn&quot;&gt;Yes / No&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Comments&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div id=&quot;accList&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;!-- V Training --&gt;
  &lt;div class=&quot;card&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;card-head&quot;&gt;V. &amp;nbsp;Training&lt;span class=&quot;sub&quot;&gt;To be performed and confirmed by customer's staff&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;card-body&quot;&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;clist-head&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;#&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Item&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;c-yn&quot;&gt;Yes / No&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Comments&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div id=&quot;trnList&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;!-- VI Post-Installation --&gt;
  &lt;div class=&quot;card&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;card-head&quot;&gt;VI. &amp;nbsp;Post-Installation Activities&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;card-body&quot;&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;clist-head&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;#&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Item&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;c-yn&quot;&gt;Yes / No&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Comments&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div id=&quot;postList&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;sigrow&quot; style=&quot;margin-top:14px;&quot;&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;field&quot;&gt;&lt;label&gt;Customer Signature (type full name)&lt;/label&gt;&lt;input class=&quot;inp sig&quot; id=&quot;vi_sig&quot; placeholder=&quot;Customer name&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;field&quot;&gt;&lt;label&gt;Date&lt;/label&gt;&lt;input type=&quot;date&quot; class=&quot;inp&quot; id=&quot;vi_date&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;!-- VII Staff Checkup --&gt;
  &lt;div class=&quot;card&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;card-head&quot;&gt;VII. &amp;nbsp;Staff Checkup and Acceptance&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;card-body&quot;&gt;
      &lt;p class=&quot;hint&quot;&gt;Type each staff member's name across the top. Tap a cell to cycle blank → &lt;b style=&quot;color:var(--green)&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/b&gt; → &lt;b style=&quot;color:var(--red)&quot;&gt;N&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;gwrap&quot;&gt;&lt;table class=&quot;grid&quot; id=&quot;vGrid&quot;&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;!-- VIII Comments --&gt;
  &lt;div class=&quot;card&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;card-head&quot;&gt;VIII. &amp;nbsp;Comments / Outstanding Issues&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;card-body&quot;&gt;
      &lt;textarea class=&quot;inp&quot; id=&quot;comments&quot; placeholder=&quot;Note any outstanding issues, follow-ups, or remarks...&quot;&gt;&lt;/textarea&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;sigrow&quot; style=&quot;margin-top:12px;&quot;&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;field&quot;&gt;&lt;label&gt;PulmOne Service Specialist — Signature (type name)&lt;/label&gt;&lt;input class=&quot;inp sig&quot; id=&quot;spec_sig&quot; placeholder=&quot;Specialist name&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;field&quot;&gt;&lt;label&gt;Date&lt;/label&gt;&lt;input type=&quot;date&quot; class=&quot;inp&quot; id=&quot;spec_date&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;!-- IX Main customer --&gt;
  &lt;div class=&quot;card&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;card-head&quot;&gt;IX. &amp;nbsp;Main Customer Person at Installation&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;card-body&quot;&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;grid2&quot; style=&quot;margin-bottom:14px;&quot;&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;field&quot;&gt;&lt;label&gt;Payment Arrangements&lt;/label&gt;&lt;input class=&quot;inp&quot; id=&quot;payment_arr&quot; placeholder=&quot;e.g. PO / financing / paid&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;field&quot;&gt;&lt;label&gt;P.O.&lt;/label&gt;&lt;input class=&quot;inp&quot; id=&quot;ix_po&quot; placeholder=&quot;PO #&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;attest&quot;&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;I confirm that I have been trained on the MiniBox(+).&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;I understand and am comfortable performing the following functions: general settings, clinical settings, report configuration, report printing / saving, calibration check, patient data entry, session start, and all patient test maneuvers; filter credits and updating sessions when a new box of filters is ordered.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;I understand that the MiniBox+ has been validated to not require internal sanitization &lt;b&gt;only&lt;/b&gt; when the PulmOne viral-bacterial filter is used in conjunction with the MiniBox+. I also understand that the clinical accuracy of the MiniBox+ requires that a PulmOne viral-bacterial filter is used in conjunction with the MiniBox+. Use of the MiniBox+ without a PulmOne viral-bacterial filter may void your warranty.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;I was also guided on how to access the customer portal and order mouthpieces and other supplies.&lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;sigrow&quot; style=&quot;margin-top:14px;&quot;&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;field&quot;&gt;&lt;label&gt;Customer Signature (type full name)&lt;/label&gt;&lt;input class=&quot;inp sig&quot; id=&quot;ix_sig&quot; placeholder=&quot;Customer name&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;field&quot;&gt;&lt;label&gt;Date&lt;/label&gt;&lt;input type=&quot;date&quot; class=&quot;inp&quot; id=&quot;ix_date&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;field&quot; style=&quot;margin-top:12px;&quot;&gt;&lt;label&gt;Print Name&lt;/label&gt;&lt;input class=&quot;inp&quot; id=&quot;ix_print&quot; placeholder=&quot;Printed name&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;

&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;script&gt;
// ---------- data ----------
var STAFF = [&quot;Primary contact person&quot;,&quot;Physician&quot;,&quot;Practice Manager&quot;,&quot;Professional #1&quot;,&quot;Professional #2&quot;,&quot;Professional #3&quot;,&quot;Professional #4&quot;,&quot;Professional #5&quot;];
var RECV = [[&quot;1&quot;,&quot;MiniBox shipping box is sealed&quot;,0],[&quot;2&quot;,&quot;Shipping contents intact:&quot;,0],
 [&quot;&quot;,&quot;MiniBox device&quot;,1],[&quot;&quot;,&quot;Handheld unit (Spirometer)&quot;,1],[&quot;&quot;,&quot;Tablet&quot;,1],[&quot;&quot;,&quot;Calibration filter&quot;,1],
 [&quot;&quot;,&quot;Documentation USB&quot;,1],[&quot;&quot;,&quot;Power and comm. cables&quot;,1],[&quot;&quot;,&quot;Mobile cart&quot;,1],[&quot;&quot;,&quot;Syringe&quot;,1],
 [&quot;&quot;,&quot;DLCO regulator&quot;,1],[&quot;&quot;,&quot;Filter pack (note Qty in comments)&quot;,1],[&quot;3&quot;,&quot;Items supplied by customer&quot;,0]];
var ACC = [[&quot;1&quot;,&quot;MiniBox system is fully assembled and power is ON&quot;,0],
 [&quot;&quot;,&quot;Touch screen turns ON and is responsive to touch&quot;,1],
 [&quot;2&quot;,&quot;DLCO regulators and tank are connected to the MiniBox&quot;,0],
 [&quot;&quot;,&quot;Regulator type (note in comments)&quot;,1],[&quot;&quot;,&quot;Pressure on gauges (note in comments)&quot;,1],
 [&quot;&quot;,&quot;Pressure targets are marked&quot;,1],[&quot;3&quot;,&quot;Cart is fully assembled&quot;,0],
 [&quot;4&quot;,&quot;Supplied accessories assembled&quot;,0],[&quot;5&quot;,&quot;Successful FVC calibration check (note error % in comments)&quot;,0],
 [&quot;6&quot;,&quot;Successful DLCO calibration check&quot;,0],[&quot;7&quot;,&quot;Successful FVC (by Service Specialist)&quot;,0],
 [&quot;8&quot;,&quot;Successful SVC (by Service Specialist)&quot;,0],[&quot;9&quot;,&quot;Successful LVM (by Service Specialist)&quot;,0],
 [&quot;10&quot;,&quot;Successful DLCO (by Service Specialist)&quot;,0],[&quot;11&quot;,&quot;Reports printed to a local printer&quot;,0],
 [&quot;12&quot;,&quot;Printer brand &amp; model (note in comments)&quot;,0],[&quot;13&quot;,&quot;All reports saved to a USB flash drive&quot;,0],
 [&quot;14&quot;,&quot;Additional setup information&quot;,0],[&quot;15&quot;,&quot;Network drive connected successfully&quot;,0],
 [&quot;16&quot;,&quot;Remote connection via TeamViewer successful&quot;,0]];
var TRN = [[&quot;1&quot;,&quot;Training conducted by PulmOne representative&quot;,0],[&quot;2&quot;,&quot;Setup and configuration&quot;,0],
 [&quot;3&quot;,&quot;Clinical settings&quot;,0],[&quot;4&quot;,&quot;System settings&quot;,0],[&quot;5&quot;,&quot;Calibration checks&quot;,0],
 [&quot;6&quot;,&quot;Patient maneuvers demonstrated by PulmOne&quot;,0],[&quot;7&quot;,&quot;Tests performed by staff on their patients:&quot;,0],
 [&quot;&quot;,&quot;FVC&quot;,1],[&quot;&quot;,&quot;SVC&quot;,1],[&quot;&quot;,&quot;MVV&quot;,1],[&quot;&quot;,&quot;LVM&quot;,1],[&quot;&quot;,&quot;DLCO&quot;,1],[&quot;&quot;,&quot;Provocation&quot;,1],
 [&quot;8&quot;,&quot;Staff comfortable with all functions; enough training time given&quot;,0]];
var POST = [[&quot;1&quot;,&quot;Review service contact details&quot;,0],
 [&quot;&quot;,&quot;PulmOne website: www.pulm-one.com&quot;,1],[&quot;&quot;,&quot;PulmOne toll-free service line: 1-844-PulmOne&quot;,1],
 [&quot;2&quot;,&quot;Create customer portal account for filter ordering (lead time 1-2 wks)&quot;,0],
 [&quot;3&quot;,&quot;Review database backup option (customer's responsibility)&quot;,0],[&quot;4&quot;,&quot;MiniBox Academy log-in&quot;,0]];
var VITEMS = [&quot;Volume calibration check&quot;,&quot;DLCO calibration check&quot;,&quot;FVC test&quot;,&quot;SVC test&quot;,&quot;MVV test&quot;,&quot;LVM test&quot;,&quot;DLCO test&quot;,&quot;Provocation test&quot;,&quot;Customer portal login access&quot;,&quot;Filter ordering procedure&quot;,&quot;MiniBox Academy signup&quot;,&quot;Contacting Customer Service&quot;,&quot;Setting up Settings&quot;,&quot;Reports printing&quot;,&quot;DLCO tanks replacement&quot;];

// ---------- builders ----------
function esc(s){return s.replace(/[^a-z0-9]/gi,'_');}
function ynHTML(key){
  return '&lt;div class=&quot;yn&quot; data-key=&quot;'+key+'&quot;&gt;'+
    '&lt;button type=&quot;button&quot; class=&quot;yn-btn yes&quot; onclick=&quot;setYN(this)&quot;&gt;Yes&lt;/button&gt;'+
    '&lt;button type=&quot;button&quot; class=&quot;yn-btn no&quot; onclick=&quot;setYN(this)&quot;&gt;No&lt;/button&gt;&lt;/div&gt;';
}
function buildList(arr, containerId, prefix){
  var h='';
  for(var i=0;i&lt;arr.length;i++){
    var no=arr[i][0], txt=arr[i][1], sub=arr[i][2];
    var key=prefix+'_'+i;
    h+='&lt;div class=&quot;item'+(sub?' sub':'')+'&quot;&gt;'+
       '&lt;div class=&quot;num&quot;&gt;'+no+'&lt;/div&gt;'+
       '&lt;div class=&quot;lbl&quot;&gt;'+txt+'&lt;/div&gt;'+
       ynHTML(key)+
       '&lt;input class=&quot;cmt&quot; id=&quot;cmt_'+key+'&quot; placeholder=&quot;Comments&quot;&gt;'+
       '&lt;/div&gt;';
  }
  document.getElementById(containerId).innerHTML=h;
}
function buildStaff(){
  var h='';
  for(var i=0;i&lt;STAFF.length;i++){
    h+='&lt;div class=&quot;staff-row&quot;&gt;'+
       '&lt;div class=&quot;role&quot;&gt;'+STAFF[i]+'&lt;/div&gt;'+
       '&lt;input class=&quot;inp&quot; id=&quot;staff'+i+'_name&quot;&gt;'+
       '&lt;input class=&quot;inp&quot; id=&quot;staff'+i+'_phone&quot;&gt;'+
       '&lt;input class=&quot;inp&quot; id=&quot;staff'+i+'_email&quot;&gt;'+
       '&lt;/div&gt;';
  }
  document.getElementById('staffRows').innerHTML=h;
}
function buildGrid(){
  var h='&lt;thead&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;th class=&quot;item-h&quot;&gt;Item \\ Staff&lt;/th&gt;';
  for(var s=0;s&lt;7;s++){ h+='&lt;th&gt;&lt;input id=&quot;gname_'+s+'&quot; placeholder=&quot;Name '+(s+1)+'&quot;&gt;&lt;/th&gt;'; }
  h+='&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/thead&gt;&lt;tbody&gt;';
  for(var r=0;r&lt;VITEMS.length;r++){
    h+='&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&quot;item-c&quot;&gt;'+VITEMS[r]+'&lt;/td&gt;';
    for(var s=0;s&lt;7;s++){ h+='&lt;td&gt;&lt;button type=&quot;button&quot; class=&quot;cyc&quot; data-key=&quot;g_'+r+'_'+s+'&quot; data-v=&quot;&quot; onclick=&quot;cycle(this)&quot;&gt;&lt;/button&gt;&lt;/td&gt;'; }
    h+='&lt;/tr&gt;';
  }
  h+='&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&quot;item-c&quot;&gt;Signatures (initials)&lt;/td&gt;';
  for(var s=0;s&lt;7;s++){ h+='&lt;td&gt;&lt;input class=&quot;grid-init&quot; id=&quot;ginit_'+s+'&quot; placeholder=&quot;—&quot;&gt;&lt;/td&gt;'; }
  h+='&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/tbody&gt;';
  document.getElementById('vGrid').innerHTML=h;
}

// ---------- interactions ----------
function setYN(btn){
  var group=btn.parentNode;
  var was=btn.classList.contains('active');
  var b=group.querySelectorAll('.yn-btn');
  b[0].classList.remove('active'); b[1].classList.remove('active');
  if(!was) btn.classList.add('active');
  save();
}
function cycle(btn){
  var v=btn.getAttribute('data-v');
  var nv = v===''?'Y':(v==='Y'?'N':'');
  btn.setAttribute('data-v',nv); btn.textContent=nv;
  save();
}

// ---------- persistence ----------
var KEY='pulmone_icf_v1';
function collect(){
  var d={inputs:{},yn:{},grid:{}};
  document.querySelectorAll('input,textarea').forEach(function(el){ if(el.id) d.inputs[el.id]=el.value; });
  document.querySelectorAll('.yn').forEach(function(g){
    var k=g.getAttribute('data-key'); var y=g.querySelector('.yes').classList.contains('active'); var n=g.querySelector('.no').classList.contains('active');
    d.yn[k]= y?'yes':(n?'no':'');
  });
  document.querySelectorAll('.cyc').forEach(function(c){ d.grid[c.getAttribute('data-key')]=c.getAttribute('data-v'); });
  return d;
}
function save(){ try{ localStorage.setItem(KEY, JSON.stringify(collect())); }catch(e){} }
function restore(){
  var raw; try{ raw=localStorage.getItem(KEY); }catch(e){ return; }
  if(!raw) return;
  var d; try{ d=JSON.parse(raw); }catch(e){ return; }
  if(d.inputs) for(var id in d.inputs){ var el=document.getElementById(id); if(el) el.value=d.inputs[id]; }
  if(d.yn) document.querySelectorAll('.yn').forEach(function(g){
    var v=d.yn[g.getAttribute('data-key')]; if(!v) return;
    g.querySelector(v==='yes'?'.yes':'.no').classList.add('active');
  });
  if(d.grid) document.querySelectorAll('.cyc').forEach(function(c){
    var v=d.grid[c.getAttribute('data-key')]; if(v){ c.setAttribute('data-v',v); c.textContent=v; }
  });
}
function clearForm(){
  if(!confirm('Clear all entries on this form?')) return;
  try{ localStorage.removeItem(KEY); }catch(e){}
  document.querySelectorAll('input,textarea').forEach(function(el){ el.value=''; });
  document.querySelectorAll('.yn-btn').forEach(function(b){ b.classList.remove('active'); });
  document.querySelectorAll('.cyc').forEach(function(c){ c.setAttribute('data-v',''); c.textContent=''; });
}

// ---------- init ----------
buildStaff();
buildList(RECV,'recvList','recv');
buildList(ACC,'accList','acc');
buildList(TRN,'trnList','trn');
buildList(POST,'postList','post');
buildGrid();
restore();
document.addEventListener('input', function(e){ if(e.target.matches('input,textarea')) save(); });
&lt;/script&gt;
&lt;script&gt;
(function(){function ph(){try{parent.postMessage({icfHeight:document.documentElement.scrollHeight},'*');}catch(e){}}
window.addEventListener('load',ph);window.addEventListener('resize',ph);
document.addEventListener('input',ph);document.addEventListener('click',ph);
try{new MutationObserver(ph).observe(document.body,{subtree:true,childList:true,attributes:true});}catch(e){}
setInterval(ph,1200);})();
&lt;/script&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;
"></iframe>
      </div>
    </div>
    <script>
      window.addEventListener('message', function(e){
        if(e.data && e.data.icfHeight){ var f=document.getElementById('icf-iframe'); if(f){ f.style.height=(e.data.icfHeight+24)+'px'; } }
      });
    </script>

    <!-- ==================== ROI PROPOSAL BUILDER (embedded) ==================== -->
    <div class="form-card" style="margin-bottom: 28px;">
      <div class="form-card-header" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0f1c35, #2563eb);">
        <div>
          <div class="form-card-title">&#128200; PulmOne ROI Proposal Builder</div>
          <div class="form-card-sub">Live ROI &middot; 5-Year Projection &middot; Printable Proposal &mdash; v2.4</div>
        </div>
        <div style="display:flex; gap:8px; align-items:center; flex-wrap:wrap;">
          <span style="font-size:11px; color:rgba(255,255,255,0.7); letter-spacing:0.06em;">EMBEDDED</span>
          <button onclick="roiBuilderFullscreen()" style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.15); border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.3); color:#fff; border-radius:6px; padding:7px 14px; font-family:'Inter',sans-serif; font-size:11.5px; font-weight:600; cursor:pointer;">&#9974; Fullscreen</button>
          <button onclick="roiBuilderPrint()" style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.15); border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.3); color:#fff; border-radius:6px; padding:7px 14px; font-family:'Inter',sans-serif; font-size:11.5px; font-weight:600; cursor:pointer;">&#128424; Print Proposal</button>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="form-body" style="padding: 0;">
        <div style="background:#f1f5f9; padding:10px 18px; font-size:12px; color:#475569; border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">
          &#9432; Fill in Practice Name and Doctor to auto-save the proposal summary. Click <strong>Fullscreen</strong> for presentation mode on an iPad or <strong>Print Proposal</strong> to save as PDF.
        </div>
        <iframe id="roi-builder-iframe"
          style="width:100%; border:0; height:1650px; display:block; background:#f1f5f9;"
          srcdoc="&lt;!doctype html&gt;
&lt;html lang=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
&lt;head&gt;
&lt;meta charset=&quot;utf-8&quot;&gt;
&lt;meta name=&quot;viewport&quot; content=&quot;width=device-width, initial-scale=1&quot;&gt;
&lt;title&gt;Spirometry / PFT Billing Helper&lt;/title&gt;
&lt;style&gt;
  :root{color-scheme:light;--navy:#1f3a5f;--navy2:#27496d;--red:#b3261e;--green:#1d7a46;
    --amber:#fff3cd;--grey:#5b6470;--line:#d8dee6;--bg:#f4f6f9;--card:#fff;--soft:#eef3f8;--warn:#fdeceb}
  *{box-sizing:border-box}
  body{margin:0;font-family:-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,&quot;Segoe UI&quot;,Arial,sans-serif;color:#1c2733;background:var(--bg);line-height:1.5}
  .wrap{max-width:940px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 18px 60px}
  header{background:linear-gradient(135deg,var(--navy),var(--navy2));color:#fff;padding:26px 0 22px;margin-bottom:22px}
  header .wrap{padding-top:0;padding-bottom:0}
  h1{margin:0 0 4px;font-size:26px}
  .sub{opacity:.88;font-size:14px;max-width:700px}
  .badge{display:inline-block;background:rgba(255,255,255,.16);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.3);font-size:11px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:20px;margin-top:8px}
  .card{background:var(--card);border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:12px;padding:20px;margin-bottom:18px;box-shadow:0 1px 2px rgba(20,40,70,.04)}
  .step{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:10px;font-weight:700;color:var(--navy);font-size:15px;margin:0 0 14px}
  .num{display:inline-flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;width:24px;height:24px;border-radius:50%;background:var(--navy);color:#fff;font-size:13px;flex:0 0 auto}
  label.fld{display:block;font-size:12px;font-weight:700;color:var(--grey);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.5px;margin-bottom:6px}
  select,.combo{width:100%;padding:11px 12px;font-size:15px;border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:8px;background:#fff;color:#1c2733;font-family:inherit}
  select:disabled,.combo:disabled{background:#f1f3f6;color:#9aa3ad}
  select:focus,.combo:focus{outline:2px solid var(--navy);outline-offset:1px}
  .combo::placeholder{color:#9aa3ad}
  .hide{display:none}
  .row{display:flex;gap:16px;flex-wrap:wrap}.row&gt;div{flex:1;min-width:200px}
  .codes{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:8px 18px;margin-top:4px}
  @media(max-width:620px){.codes{grid-template-columns:1fr}}
  .chk{display:flex;gap:9px;align-items:flex-start;font-size:14px;padding:8px 10px;border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:8px;cursor:pointer;background:#fff}
  .chk:hover{background:var(--soft)}.chk input{margin-top:3px}.chk b{font-variant-numeric:tabular-nums}
  .chk small{display:block;color:var(--grey);font-size:12px}
  .chk.off{opacity:.5;cursor:not-allowed;background:#f7f8fa}
  .chk .note{display:none;color:var(--red);font-size:11.5px;font-weight:700;margin-top:3px}
  .chk .note.on{display:block}
  .codestatus{margin-top:10px;font-size:13px;font-weight:800;color:var(--green)}
  .toggle{display:flex;gap:10px;align-items:center;padding:12px;border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:8px;margin-top:12px;background:var(--soft)}
  .toggle input{width:18px;height:18px}.opts{margin-top:12px}.opts .chk{margin-bottom:6px;cursor:default}
  button.go{margin-top:16px;background:var(--red);color:#fff;border:0;padding:13px 22px;font-size:15px;font-weight:700;border-radius:8px;cursor:pointer}
  button.go:hover{filter:brightness(1.07)}
  .btns{display:flex;gap:10px;flex-wrap:wrap;align-items:center}
  button.ghost{margin-top:16px;background:#fff;color:var(--navy);border:1px solid var(--navy);padding:13px 18px;font-size:14px;font-weight:700;border-radius:8px;cursor:pointer}
  #out{display:none}
  .mac{display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:14px;align-items:center;background:var(--soft);border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:10px;padding:14px 16px;margin-bottom:16px}
  .mac .big{font-size:19px;font-weight:800;color:var(--navy)}
  .mac .jur{font-size:12px;color:var(--grey);font-weight:700;letter-spacing:.5px;text-transform:uppercase}
  .res-h{font-size:13px;font-weight:800;color:var(--navy);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.6px;margin:22px 0 8px;border-bottom:2px solid var(--navy);padding-bottom:4px}
  ol.steps{padding-left:20px;margin:6px 0}ol.steps li{margin-bottom:9px}
  ul.chklist{list-style:none;padding:0;margin:6px 0}
  ul.chklist li{padding:5px 0 5px 26px;position:relative;font-size:14px}
  ul.chklist li:before{content:&quot;\2713&quot;;position:absolute;left:0;top:4px;color:var(--green);font-weight:800}
  .pill{display:inline-block;font-size:12px;font-weight:700;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:5px;vertical-align:middle}
  .pill.code{background:var(--navy);color:#fff;font-variant-numeric:tabular-nums}
  .pill.mod{background:#fde8e6;color:var(--red);border:1px solid #f3c2bd}
  .pill.dx{background:#e7eef6;color:var(--navy);border:1px solid #c4d4e6}
  .verify{background:var(--amber);border-left:5px solid var(--red);border-radius:6px;padding:12px 14px;margin:12px 0;font-size:13.5px}
  .verify b{color:var(--red)}
  .warnbox{background:var(--warn);border-left:5px solid var(--red);border-radius:6px;padding:12px 14px;margin:10px 0;font-size:14px}
  .warnbox b{color:var(--red)}
  .claim{background:#0f1b2b;color:#e8eef6;border-radius:10px;padding:14px 16px;font-family:&quot;SF Mono&quot;,Consolas,Menlo,monospace;font-size:14px;margin:8px 0}
  .claim .ln{display:flex;gap:10px;align-items:baseline;padding:5px 0;border-bottom:1px solid #24364c}
  .claim .ln:last-child{border-bottom:0}
  .claim .c{color:#7fd1a0;font-weight:700;min-width:96px}
  .claim .m{color:#ff9a90;font-weight:700}
  .claim .d{color:#9fc2e8;margin-left:auto;font-size:12.5px;text-align:right}
  a{color:var(--navy);font-weight:600}
  .muted{color:var(--grey);font-size:12.5px}
  .foot{font-size:12px;color:var(--grey);border-top:1px solid var(--line);margin-top:24px;padding-top:14px}
  .err{color:var(--red);font-weight:700;font-size:13px;margin-top:8px;display:none}
  .tag{display:inline-block;font-size:11px;font-weight:700;padding:2px 9px;border-radius:20px;margin-left:8px;vertical-align:middle}
  .tag.med{background:#e7eef6;color:var(--navy)}.tag.com{background:#efe7f6;color:#5a2a82}
  @media print{header{background:var(--navy)!important;-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;print-color-adjust:exact}
    .input-card,.aboutcard{display:none}button{display:none}body{background:#fff}
    .claim{-webkit-print-color-adjust:exact;print-color-adjust:exact}}
&lt;/style&gt;
&lt;meta name=&quot;theme-color&quot; content=&quot;#1f3a5f&quot;&gt;
&lt;meta name=&quot;mobile-web-app-capable&quot; content=&quot;yes&quot;&gt;
&lt;meta name=&quot;apple-mobile-web-app-capable&quot; content=&quot;yes&quot;&gt;
&lt;meta name=&quot;apple-mobile-web-app-status-bar-style&quot; content=&quot;black-translucent&quot;&gt;
&lt;meta name=&quot;apple-mobile-web-app-title&quot; content=&quot;PFT Billing&quot;&gt;
&lt;meta name=&quot;application-name&quot; content=&quot;PFT Billing&quot;&gt;
&lt;link rel=&quot;apple-touch-icon&quot; href=&quot;data:image/png;base64,&quot;&gt;
&lt;link rel=&quot;icon&quot; type=&quot;image/png&quot; href=&quot;data:image/png;base64,&quot;&gt;
&lt;link rel=&quot;manifest&quot; href=&quot;data:application/json;base64,&quot;&gt;
&lt;/head&gt;
&lt;body&gt;
&lt;header&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;wrap&quot;&gt;
  &lt;h1&gt;Spirometry / PFT Billing Helper&lt;/h1&gt;
  &lt;div class=&quot;sub&quot;&gt;For billers. Pick the state and payer type, check what was performed, and get the exact claim. Codes that can&#39;t be billed together grey out as you go.&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;span class=&quot;badge&quot;&gt;v6 - Live conflict checks - Verify against the payer&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/header&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;wrap&quot;&gt;
  &lt;div class=&quot;card input-card&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;step&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;num&quot;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt; Where, and who&#39;s the payer?&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;row&quot;&gt;
      &lt;div&gt;
        &lt;label class=&quot;fld&quot; for=&quot;state&quot;&gt;State / territory&lt;/label&gt;
        &lt;select id=&quot;state&quot;&gt;&lt;option value=&quot;&quot;&gt;— Select state —&lt;/option&gt;&lt;/select&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div&gt;
        &lt;label class=&quot;fld&quot; for=&quot;ptype&quot;&gt;Payer type&lt;/label&gt;
        &lt;select id=&quot;ptype&quot; disabled&gt;
          &lt;option value=&quot;&quot;&gt;— pick a state first —&lt;/option&gt;
        &lt;/select&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div&gt;
        &lt;label class=&quot;fld&quot; for=&quot;proc&quot;&gt;Procedure family&lt;/label&gt;
        &lt;select id=&quot;proc&quot;&gt;&lt;/select&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div id=&quot;insurerWrap&quot; class=&quot;hide&quot; style=&quot;margin-top:14px&quot;&gt;
      &lt;label class=&quot;fld&quot; for=&quot;insurer&quot;&gt;Commercial insurer &lt;span style=&quot;text-transform:none;font-weight:600;color:#9aa3ad&quot;&gt;(type to search — optional)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/label&gt;
      &lt;input id=&quot;insurer&quot; class=&quot;combo&quot; list=&quot;insurerlist&quot; autocomplete=&quot;off&quot; placeholder=&quot;e.g. Aetna, Florida Blue — or leave blank&quot;&gt;
      &lt;datalist id=&quot;insurerlist&quot;&gt;&lt;/datalist&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;err&quot; id=&quot;err&quot;&gt;Please choose a state and payer type.&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;div class=&quot;card input-card&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;step&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;num&quot;&gt;2&lt;/span&gt; What was performed today?&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;label class=&quot;fld&quot;&gt;Test / codes performed&lt;/label&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;codes&quot; id=&quot;codes&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;codestatus&quot; id=&quot;codestatus&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;toggle&quot;&gt;
      &lt;input type=&quot;checkbox&quot; id=&quot;em&quot;&gt;
      &lt;label for=&quot;em&quot; style=&quot;margin:0;cursor:pointer&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;An office visit (E/M) was also done today&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;
      &lt;small class=&quot;muted&quot;&gt;Check this only if the provider evaluated the patient beyond running the test.&lt;/small&gt;&lt;/label&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;opts&quot;&gt;
      &lt;label class=&quot;fld&quot; style=&quot;margin-top:14px&quot;&gt;Who owns the equipment &amp;amp; reads the result?&lt;/label&gt;
      &lt;label class=&quot;chk&quot;&gt;&lt;input type=&quot;radio&quot; name=&quot;own&quot; value=&quot;global&quot; checked&gt;
        &lt;span&gt;&lt;b&gt;Practice owns the machine AND the provider interprets&lt;/b&gt;&lt;small&gt;In-office testing — bill the global service (most common)&lt;/small&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/label&gt;
      &lt;label class=&quot;chk&quot;&gt;&lt;input type=&quot;radio&quot; name=&quot;own&quot; value=&quot;pro&quot;&gt;
        &lt;span&gt;&lt;b&gt;Provider only interprets&lt;/b&gt; (equipment owned elsewhere)&lt;small&gt;Bill professional component only&lt;/small&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/label&gt;
      &lt;label class=&quot;chk&quot;&gt;&lt;input type=&quot;radio&quot; name=&quot;own&quot; value=&quot;tech&quot;&gt;
        &lt;span&gt;&lt;b&gt;Practice only provides equipment/technician&lt;/b&gt;&lt;small&gt;Bill technical component only&lt;/small&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/label&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;btns&quot;&gt;
      &lt;button class=&quot;go&quot; id=&quot;run&quot;&gt;Build my claim &amp;rarr;&lt;/button&gt;
      &lt;button class=&quot;ghost&quot; id=&quot;print&quot; style=&quot;display:none&quot;&gt;Print / Save PDF&lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;div class=&quot;card&quot; id=&quot;out&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;mac&quot; id=&quot;macCard&quot;&gt;
      &lt;div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;jur&quot; id=&quot;jurLabel&quot;&gt;Payer&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;big&quot; id=&quot;macName&quot;&gt;—&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div style=&quot;text-align:right;flex:1&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;jur&quot; id=&quot;jurTitle&quot;&gt;Processed by&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;big&quot; id=&quot;jurName&quot;&gt;—&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div id=&quot;result&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;foot&quot; id=&quot;disclaimer&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;div class=&quot;card aboutcard&quot; style=&quot;background:var(--soft)&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;step&quot; style=&quot;margin-bottom:8px&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;num&quot; style=&quot;background:var(--grey)&quot;&gt;i&lt;/span&gt; About this tool&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;p class=&quot;muted&quot; style=&quot;margin:0&quot;&gt;A &lt;b&gt;living helper&lt;/b&gt;. Codes that can&#39;t be billed together (bundled or mutually exclusive under NCCI) grey out the moment you select the one that controls them, so you only ever build a valid combination. &lt;b&gt;Each payer&#39;s covered-diagnosis list and frequency rules vary and are not hard-coded&lt;/b&gt; — the tool routes you to that payer&#39;s own policy to confirm before you submit.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;script&gt;
/* ===================== DATA ENGINE ===================== */
var MACS={palmetto:&quot;Palmetto GBA&quot;,novitas:&quot;Novitas Solutions&quot;,firstcoast:&quot;First Coast Service Options&quot;,
  ngs:&quot;National Government Services (NGS)&quot;,wps:&quot;WPS (Wisconsin Physicians Service)&quot;,cgs:&quot;CGS Administrators&quot;,
  noridian:&quot;Noridian Healthcare Solutions&quot;};
var STATES={
  &quot;Alabama&quot;:[&quot;palmetto&quot;,&quot;JJ&quot;],&quot;Alaska&quot;:[&quot;noridian&quot;,&quot;JF&quot;],&quot;Arizona&quot;:[&quot;noridian&quot;,&quot;JF&quot;],&quot;Arkansas&quot;:[&quot;novitas&quot;,&quot;JH&quot;],
  &quot;California&quot;:[&quot;noridian&quot;,&quot;JE&quot;],&quot;Colorado&quot;:[&quot;novitas&quot;,&quot;JH&quot;],&quot;Connecticut&quot;:[&quot;ngs&quot;,&quot;JK&quot;],&quot;Delaware&quot;:[&quot;novitas&quot;,&quot;JL&quot;],
  &quot;District of Columbia&quot;:[&quot;novitas&quot;,&quot;JL&quot;],&quot;Florida&quot;:[&quot;firstcoast&quot;,&quot;JN&quot;],&quot;Georgia&quot;:[&quot;palmetto&quot;,&quot;JJ&quot;],&quot;Hawaii&quot;:[&quot;noridian&quot;,&quot;JE&quot;],
  &quot;Idaho&quot;:[&quot;noridian&quot;,&quot;JF&quot;],&quot;Illinois&quot;:[&quot;ngs&quot;,&quot;J6&quot;],&quot;Indiana&quot;:[&quot;wps&quot;,&quot;J8&quot;],&quot;Iowa&quot;:[&quot;wps&quot;,&quot;J5&quot;],&quot;Kansas&quot;:[&quot;wps&quot;,&quot;J5&quot;],
  &quot;Kentucky&quot;:[&quot;cgs&quot;,&quot;J15&quot;],&quot;Louisiana&quot;:[&quot;novitas&quot;,&quot;JH&quot;],&quot;Maine&quot;:[&quot;ngs&quot;,&quot;JK&quot;],&quot;Maryland&quot;:[&quot;novitas&quot;,&quot;JL&quot;],
  &quot;Massachusetts&quot;:[&quot;ngs&quot;,&quot;JK&quot;],&quot;Michigan&quot;:[&quot;wps&quot;,&quot;J8&quot;],&quot;Minnesota&quot;:[&quot;ngs&quot;,&quot;J6&quot;],&quot;Mississippi&quot;:[&quot;novitas&quot;,&quot;JH&quot;],
  &quot;Missouri&quot;:[&quot;wps&quot;,&quot;J5&quot;],&quot;Montana&quot;:[&quot;noridian&quot;,&quot;JF&quot;],&quot;Nebraska&quot;:[&quot;wps&quot;,&quot;J5&quot;],&quot;Nevada&quot;:[&quot;noridian&quot;,&quot;JE&quot;],
  &quot;New Hampshire&quot;:[&quot;ngs&quot;,&quot;JK&quot;],&quot;New Jersey&quot;:[&quot;novitas&quot;,&quot;JL&quot;],&quot;New Mexico&quot;:[&quot;novitas&quot;,&quot;JH&quot;],&quot;New York&quot;:[&quot;ngs&quot;,&quot;JK&quot;],
  &quot;North Carolina&quot;:[&quot;palmetto&quot;,&quot;JM&quot;],&quot;North Dakota&quot;:[&quot;noridian&quot;,&quot;JF&quot;],&quot;Ohio&quot;:[&quot;cgs&quot;,&quot;J15&quot;],&quot;Oklahoma&quot;:[&quot;novitas&quot;,&quot;JH&quot;],
  &quot;Oregon&quot;:[&quot;noridian&quot;,&quot;JF&quot;],&quot;Pennsylvania&quot;:[&quot;novitas&quot;,&quot;JL&quot;],&quot;Rhode Island&quot;:[&quot;ngs&quot;,&quot;JK&quot;],&quot;South Carolina&quot;:[&quot;palmetto&quot;,&quot;JM&quot;],
  &quot;South Dakota&quot;:[&quot;noridian&quot;,&quot;JF&quot;],&quot;Tennessee&quot;:[&quot;palmetto&quot;,&quot;JJ&quot;],&quot;Texas&quot;:[&quot;novitas&quot;,&quot;JH&quot;],&quot;Utah&quot;:[&quot;noridian&quot;,&quot;JF&quot;],
  &quot;Vermont&quot;:[&quot;ngs&quot;,&quot;JK&quot;],&quot;Virginia&quot;:[&quot;palmetto&quot;,&quot;JM&quot;],&quot;Washington&quot;:[&quot;noridian&quot;,&quot;JF&quot;],&quot;West Virginia&quot;:[&quot;palmetto&quot;,&quot;JM&quot;],
  &quot;Wisconsin&quot;:[&quot;ngs&quot;,&quot;J6&quot;],&quot;Wyoming&quot;:[&quot;noridian&quot;,&quot;JF&quot;],&quot;Puerto Rico&quot;:[&quot;firstcoast&quot;,&quot;JN&quot;],&quot;U.S. Virgin Islands&quot;:[&quot;firstcoast&quot;,&quot;JN&quot;],
  &quot;Guam / American Samoa / N. Mariana Is.&quot;:[&quot;noridian&quot;,&quot;JE&quot;]
};
var MEDICAID={
  &quot;Alabama&quot;:&quot;Alabama Medicaid&quot;,&quot;Alaska&quot;:&quot;Alaska Medicaid (DenaliCare)&quot;,&quot;Arizona&quot;:&quot;AHCCCS&quot;,&quot;Arkansas&quot;:&quot;Arkansas Medicaid&quot;,
  &quot;California&quot;:&quot;Medi-Cal&quot;,&quot;Colorado&quot;:&quot;Health First Colorado&quot;,&quot;Connecticut&quot;:&quot;HUSKY Health&quot;,&quot;Delaware&quot;:&quot;Delaware Medicaid&quot;,
  &quot;District of Columbia&quot;:&quot;DC Medicaid&quot;,&quot;Florida&quot;:&quot;Florida Medicaid&quot;,&quot;Georgia&quot;:&quot;Georgia Medicaid&quot;,&quot;Hawaii&quot;:&quot;Med-QUEST&quot;,
  &quot;Idaho&quot;:&quot;Idaho Medicaid&quot;,&quot;Illinois&quot;:&quot;Illinois Medicaid&quot;,&quot;Indiana&quot;:&quot;Indiana Health Coverage Programs (IHCP)&quot;,&quot;Iowa&quot;:&quot;IA Health Link&quot;,
  &quot;Kansas&quot;:&quot;KanCare&quot;,&quot;Kentucky&quot;:&quot;Kentucky Medicaid&quot;,&quot;Louisiana&quot;:&quot;Healthy Louisiana&quot;,&quot;Maine&quot;:&quot;MaineCare&quot;,
  &quot;Maryland&quot;:&quot;Maryland Medical Assistance&quot;,&quot;Massachusetts&quot;:&quot;MassHealth&quot;,&quot;Michigan&quot;:&quot;Michigan Medicaid&quot;,&quot;Minnesota&quot;:&quot;Medical Assistance (MN)&quot;,
  &quot;Mississippi&quot;:&quot;Mississippi Medicaid&quot;,&quot;Missouri&quot;:&quot;MO HealthNet&quot;,&quot;Montana&quot;:&quot;Montana Medicaid&quot;,&quot;Nebraska&quot;:&quot;Nebraska Medicaid&quot;,
  &quot;Nevada&quot;:&quot;Nevada Medicaid&quot;,&quot;New Hampshire&quot;:&quot;New Hampshire Medicaid&quot;,&quot;New Jersey&quot;:&quot;NJ FamilyCare&quot;,&quot;New Mexico&quot;:&quot;Centennial Care&quot;,
  &quot;New York&quot;:&quot;New York Medicaid&quot;,&quot;North Carolina&quot;:&quot;NC Medicaid&quot;,&quot;North Dakota&quot;:&quot;North Dakota Medicaid&quot;,&quot;Ohio&quot;:&quot;Ohio Medicaid&quot;,
  &quot;Oklahoma&quot;:&quot;SoonerCare&quot;,&quot;Oregon&quot;:&quot;Oregon Health Plan (OHP)&quot;,&quot;Pennsylvania&quot;:&quot;Medical Assistance (PA)&quot;,&quot;Rhode Island&quot;:&quot;Rhode Island Medicaid&quot;,
  &quot;South Carolina&quot;:&quot;Healthy Connections&quot;,&quot;South Dakota&quot;:&quot;South Dakota Medicaid&quot;,&quot;Tennessee&quot;:&quot;TennCare&quot;,&quot;Texas&quot;:&quot;Texas Medicaid&quot;,
  &quot;Utah&quot;:&quot;Utah Medicaid&quot;,&quot;Vermont&quot;:&quot;Vermont Medicaid&quot;,&quot;Virginia&quot;:&quot;Cardinal Care&quot;,&quot;Washington&quot;:&quot;Apple Health&quot;,
  &quot;West Virginia&quot;:&quot;West Virginia Medicaid&quot;,&quot;Wisconsin&quot;:&quot;BadgerCare Plus&quot;,&quot;Wyoming&quot;:&quot;Wyoming Medicaid&quot;,
  &quot;Puerto Rico&quot;:&quot;Puerto Rico Medicaid&quot;,&quot;U.S. Virgin Islands&quot;:&quot;USVI Medicaid&quot;,&quot;Guam / American Samoa / N. Mariana Is.&quot;:&quot;Territory Medicaid&quot;
};
var CLASS_DX={
  medicare:&quot;Medicare does NOT require a different diagnosis for the E/M than the test - Modifier 25 just needs a documented, separate evaluation.&quot;,
  ma:&quot;MA plans cover at least what Medicare covers and follow the same NCCI/Modifier 25 rules - but each plan adds its own edits and prior-auth. Use the Medicare LCD as the floor, then check the plan policy.&quot;,
  commercial:&quot;Many commercial payers deny the E/M as bundled when it shares the SAME primary diagnosis as the test. Where clinically supported, point the E/M to the evaluation diagnosis and the test to the respiratory diagnosis - and confirm this payer&#39;s Modifier 25 / reimbursement policy.&quot;,
  medicaid:&quot;Medicaid coverage, covered diagnoses, and modifier rules are set by the state and can be stricter than Medicare. Verify against the state program&#39;s provider manual / fee schedule.&quot;
};
function gsearch(q){return &quot;https://www.google.com/search?q=&quot;+encodeURIComponent(q);}
var MCD=&quot;https://www.cms.gov/medicare-coverage-database/search.aspx&quot;;

var PROCEDURES={
  pft:{
    label:&quot;Spirometry / Pulmonary Function Test&quot;,
    emExample:&quot;99214&quot;,
    codes:[
      {cpt:&quot;94010&quot;,desc:&quot;Spirometry (FVC, FEV1) - single set&quot;},
      {cpt:&quot;94060&quot;,desc:&quot;Spirometry pre &amp; post bronchodilator&quot;,includesCodes:[&quot;94010&quot;]},
      {cpt:&quot;94070&quot;,desc:&quot;Multiple/repeat spirometry (provocation)&quot;,includesCodes:[&quot;94010&quot;]},
      {cpt:&quot;94375&quot;,desc:&quot;Flow-volume loop&quot;},
      {cpt:&quot;94726&quot;,desc:&quot;Lung volumes - plethysmography&quot;},
      {cpt:&quot;94727&quot;,desc:&quot;Lung volumes - gas dilution/washout&quot;},
      {cpt:&quot;94729&quot;,desc:&quot;Diffusing capacity (DLCO) - ADD-ON&quot;,addon:true,primaries:[&quot;94010&quot;,&quot;94060&quot;,&quot;94070&quot;,&quot;94375&quot;,&quot;94726&quot;,&quot;94727&quot;]}
    ],
    mutex:[{codes:[&quot;94726&quot;,&quot;94727&quot;],keep:&quot;94726&quot;,msg:&quot;Bill only ONE lung-volume method. 94726 (plethysmography) and 94727 (gas dilution/washout) measure the same thing (lung volumes) two different ways - NCCI treats them as one and bundles them. Report the method actually performed (keeping 94726 here); billing both denies unless you have documentation of two genuinely distinct techniques.&quot;}],
    dxExamples:&quot;J44.9 (COPD), J45.909 (asthma), R06.02 (shortness of breath), R05.9 (cough), J98.4 (other lung disorder), Z01.811 (pre-op respiratory exam)&quot;,
    docChecklist:[
      &quot;Order/referral + medical reason for the test (symptoms, monitoring, pre-op, etc.)&quot;,
      &quot;Signed interpretation &amp; report - numeric values, the graphic record, and the provider&#39;s reading&quot;,
      &quot;Diagnosis code(s) that genuinely support medical necessity (a vague code alone often denies)&quot;,
      &quot;Repeat test: document why again (change in symptoms, status, or treatment decision)&quot;,
      &quot;If a visit is billed too: the note shows a separate, significant evaluation beyond the test&quot;
    ]
  }
};
