  <!-- ============================================ -->
  <!-- KEY MESSAGES BY DISCIPLINE (v2.4)            -->
  <!-- ============================================ -->
  <div class="tab-panel" id="tab-keymsg">
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="section-icon" style="background:#ffe4e6;">&#127919;</div>
      <div>
        <div class="section-title">Key Messages by Discipline</div>
        <div class="section-sub">Pain point &rarr; hero message &rarr; proof &rarr; objection handler &rarr; CTA. Tailor your opener to the specialty in front of you.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card" style="border-left:4px solid #e11d48; background:#fff1f2; margin-bottom:16px;">
      <div class="card-title" style="color:#9f1239;">&#9888; PLACEHOLDER FRAMEWORK &mdash; TEAM TO REFINE</div>
      <div class="card-body" style="color:#9f1239;">Draft messaging below is a starting point based on the MiniBox+ value proposition. Marketing + Clinical should review and lock each discipline's version before national rollout.</div>
    </div>

    <!-- PULMONOLOGY -->
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="section-icon icon-blue">&#129729;</div>
      <div><div class="section-title">Pulmonology</div><div class="section-sub">Your primary call point &mdash; they own the PFT lab</div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="card-grid grid-2" style="margin-bottom:16px;">
      <div class="card" style="border-left:4px solid var(--blue-brand);">
        <div class="card-title">Pain Point</div>
        <div class="card-body">Legacy body-box is expensive, room-sized, and booked out weeks. Tech-dependent, hard to staff, patients reschedule.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card" style="border-left:4px solid var(--blue-brand);">
        <div class="card-title">Hero Message</div>
        <div class="card-body"><strong>"Full PFTs &mdash; spirometry, lung volumes, DLCO &mdash; in the exam room, in under 15 minutes, without a sealed booth."</strong></div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title">Proof Point</div>
        <div class="card-body">CHEST 2021 Berger et al. validation study &mdash; MiniBox+ TLC vs. plethysmography in 100+ subjects. Same-day workup enables faster Rx decisions.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title">Top Objection + Handler</div>
        <div class="card-body"><em>"We already have a body box."</em> &rarr; "Perfect. MiniBox+ is for satellite offices and overflow days &mdash; you keep the box for complex cases and recover weeks of scheduling capacity."</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card" style="grid-column:1/-1; background:#eff6ff;">
        <div class="card-title">Call To Action</div>
        <div class="card-body">Schedule a 30-minute in-office demo. Bring a Berger reprint and your ROI calculator.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="divider"></div>

    <!-- ALLERGY / IMMUNOLOGY -->
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="section-icon icon-teal">&#127793;</div>
      <div><div class="section-title">Allergy / Immunology</div><div class="section-sub">Asthma workup volume &mdash; MiniBox+ adds lung volumes without a booth</div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="card-grid grid-2" style="margin-bottom:16px;">
      <div class="card" style="border-left:4px solid var(--teal);">
        <div class="card-title">Pain Point</div>
        <div class="card-body">Running spirometry only &mdash; referring out for lung volumes / DLCO loses patients and revenue.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card" style="border-left:4px solid var(--teal);">
        <div class="card-title">Hero Message</div>
        <div class="card-body"><strong>"Keep your asthma patients in-house with full PFTs &mdash; not just spirometry. One device. One visit. Full 94010 + 94726 + 94729 billing."</strong></div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title">Proof Point</div>
        <div class="card-body">Asthma/COPD overlap patients need lung volumes to distinguish obstructive from restrictive. Air trapping detection changes Rx.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title">Top Objection + Handler</div>
        <div class="card-body"><em>"We just send them for a formal PFT."</em> &rarr; "How many actually go? MiniBox+ captures the 40%+ who no-show the referral &mdash; that's both clinical follow-through and billable revenue."</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card" style="grid-column:1/-1; background:#ecfdf5;">
        <div class="card-title">Call To Action</div>
        <div class="card-body">Demo + ROI calc showing incremental 94726/94729 revenue at their current spirometry volume.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="divider"></div>

    <!-- PRIMARY CARE -->
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="section-icon icon-amber">&#127973;</div>
      <div><div class="section-title">Primary Care / Family Medicine</div><div class="section-sub">Underpenetrated segment &mdash; lead with CPT revenue, not clinical depth</div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="card-grid grid-2" style="margin-bottom:16px;">
      <div class="card" style="border-left:4px solid var(--amber);">
        <div class="card-title">Pain Point</div>
        <div class="card-body">Chronic cough, dyspnea, smoking history &mdash; all referred out. Loses patients, loses revenue, delays diagnosis.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card" style="border-left:4px solid var(--amber);">
        <div class="card-title">Hero Message</div>
        <div class="card-body"><strong>"Add a revenue line. Diagnose COPD and asthma at the point of care. ~$150 per full PFT, 10&ndash;15 minutes, staff-friendly."</strong></div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title">Proof Point</div>
        <div class="card-body">3 PFTs/week &times; 48 weeks = ~$21,700/year incremental revenue. Device pays for itself in under 18 months.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title">Top Objection + Handler</div>
        <div class="card-body"><em>"We're not a PFT lab."</em> &rarr; "You don't need to be. MiniBox+ was built for exam-room use. Your MA runs it. Results in the EMR in minutes."</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card" style="grid-column:1/-1; background:#fef3e2;">
        <div class="card-title">Call To Action</div>
        <div class="card-body">Lead with the ROI calculator (Daily Hub tab). Demo is secondary &mdash; revenue story closes them.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="divider"></div>

    <!-- CARDIOLOGY -->
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="section-icon" style="background:#fee2e2;">&#10084;</div>
      <div><div class="section-title">Cardiology</div><div class="section-sub">Dyspnea workup &mdash; rule out pulmonary before sending to stress</div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="card-grid grid-2" style="margin-bottom:16px;">
      <div class="card" style="border-left:4px solid #dc2626;">
        <div class="card-title">Pain Point</div>
        <div class="card-body">Dyspnea is cardiac vs. pulmonary until proven otherwise. Sending every patient out for PFTs delays workup.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card" style="border-left:4px solid #dc2626;">
        <div class="card-title">Hero Message</div>
        <div class="card-body"><strong>"Rule out pulmonary at the same visit. Full PFTs before the stress test, not three weeks later."</strong></div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title">Proof Point</div>
        <div class="card-body">CHF with restrictive pattern, obesity hypoventilation, and COPD overlap are all identified faster with in-office PFTs.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title">Top Objection + Handler</div>
        <div class="card-body"><em>"That's what the pulmonologist is for."</em> &rarr; "Agreed &mdash; for complex cases. MiniBox+ is your first-pass screen to decide who needs a pulm referral and who doesn't."</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card" style="grid-column:1/-1; background:#fef2f2;">
        <div class="card-title">Call To Action</div>
        <div class="card-body">Target practices running in-office stress testing &mdash; they already value same-visit diagnostics.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="divider"></div>

    <!-- PEDIATRICS -->
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="section-icon" style="background:#dbeafe;">&#129489;&#8205;&#9877;</div>
      <div><div class="section-title">Pediatrics</div><div class="section-sub">School-age asthma &mdash; kids can perform the test, booths intimidate</div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="card-grid grid-2" style="margin-bottom:16px;">
      <div class="card" style="border-left:4px solid #2563eb;">
        <div class="card-title">Pain Point</div>
        <div class="card-body">Pediatric asthma management runs on symptom diaries. Objective lung function data is rare &mdash; booths scare kids.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card" style="border-left:4px solid #2563eb;">
        <div class="card-title">Hero Message</div>
        <div class="card-body"><strong>"Open-format PFTs your patients aren't afraid of. Objective asthma control data, without sealing a 7-year-old in a box."</strong></div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title">Proof Point</div>
        <div class="card-body">MiniBox+ pediatric usability data &mdash; non-booth design, shorter test time, higher first-attempt success.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title">Top Objection + Handler</div>
        <div class="card-body"><em>"Insurance coverage for kids?"</em> &rarr; "94010/94726/94729 codes are age-agnostic. School-age kids clear cleanly on commercial and Medicaid."</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card" style="grid-column:1/-1; background:#eff6ff;">
        <div class="card-title">Call To Action</div>
        <div class="card-body">Target large multi-provider pediatric practices with asthma programs. Clinical champion = the asthma lead.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="divider"></div>

    <!-- OCCUPATIONAL MEDICINE -->
    <div class="section-head">
      <div class="section-icon" style="background:#fef3c7;">&#128736;</div>
      <div><div class="section-title">Occupational Medicine</div><div class="section-sub">OSHA respiratory surveillance &mdash; high-volume, protocol-driven</div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="card-grid grid-2">
      <div class="card" style="border-left:4px solid #d97706;">
        <div class="card-title">Pain Point</div>
        <div class="card-body">OSHA 29 CFR 1910.134 respiratory clearance &mdash; hundreds of spirometries, but missing the lung volume component for full workup.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card" style="border-left:4px solid #d97706;">
        <div class="card-title">Hero Message</div>
        <div class="card-body"><strong>"Upgrade your surveillance from spirometry to full PFT &mdash; same test time, same throughput, catches restrictive disease OSHA spirometry misses."</strong></div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title">Proof Point</div>
        <div class="card-body">Silica, asbestos, and dust exposures are restrictive patterns. Spirometry alone under-detects. Lung volumes + DLCO = complete.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-title">Top Objection + Handler</div>
        <div class="card-body"><em>"Employers won't pay for more."</em> &rarr; "You don't bill the employer &mdash; you bill the symptomatic patient's insurance when the surveillance spirometry is abnormal. New revenue line, not employer cost."</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card" style="grid-column:1/-1; background:#fffbeb;">
        <div class="card-title">Call To Action</div>
        <div class="card-body">Target large occ-med clinics with OSHA surveillance contracts. Demo throughput &mdash; they care about tests/day.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

